item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwPrimaryPowerSupplyFailure
item.description: A btSwPrimaryPowerSupplyFailure trap signifies that the primary power supply failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwDefGwUp
item.description: A btSwDefGwUp trap signifies that the default gateway is alive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwDefGwDown
item.description: A btSwDefGwDown trap signifies that the default gateway is down

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwDefGwInService
item.description: A btSwDefGwEnabled trap signifies that the default gateway is up and in service

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwDefGwNotInService
item.description: A btSwDefGwDisabled trap signifies that the default gateway is alive but not in service

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwVrrpNewMaster
item.description: The btSwVrrpNewMaster trap indicates that the sending agent has transitioned to 'Master' state

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwVrrpNewBackup
item.description: The btSwVrrpNewBackup trap indicates that the sending agent has transitioned to 'Backup' state

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwVrrpAuthFailure
item.description: A btSwVrrpAuthFailure trap signifies that a packet has been received from a router whose authentication key or authentication type conflicts with this router's authentication key or authentication type Implementation of this trap is optional

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwLoginFailure
item.description: A btSwLoginFailure trap signifies that someone failed to enter a valid usernamepassword combination

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwTempExceedThreshold
item.description: A btSwTempExceedThreshold trap signifies that the switch temperature has exceeded maximum safety limits

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwRackLocationChange
item.description: A btSwRackLocationChange trap signifies that the rack location has been changed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwApplyComplete
item.description: A btSwApplyComplete signifies that new configuration has been applied

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwSaveComplete
item.description: A btSwApplyComplete signifies that new configuration has been saved

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwFwDownloadSucess
item.description: A btSwFwDownloadSuccess signifies that firmware has been downloaded to [image|image|boot image]

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwFwDownloadFailure
item.description: A btSwFwDownloadFailure signifies that firmware downloaded failed to [image|image|boot image]

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwTempReturnThreshold
item.description: A btSwTempReturnThreshold trap signifies that the switch temperature has returned below maximum safety limits

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwFanFailure
item.description: A btSwFanFailure trap signifies that the fan failure has been detected

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwFanFailureFixed
item.description: A btSwFanFailureFixed trap signifies that the fan failure has been fixed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwUfdfoLtMFailure
item.description: A btSwUfdfoLtMFailure trap signifies that a LtM link is down

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwUfdfoLtMUP
item.description: A btSwUfdfoLtMUP trap signifies that a LtM link is up

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwUfdfoGlobalEna
item.description: A btSwUfdfoGlobalEna trap signifies that Global UFD is enabled

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwUfdfoGlobalDis
item.description: A btSwUfdfoGlobalDis trap signifies that Global UFD is disabled

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwUfdfoLtDAutoEna
item.description: A btSwUfdfoLtDAutoEna trap signifies that a LtD link is Auto Enabled

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwUfdfoLtDAutoDis
item.description: A btSwUfdfoLtDAutoDis trap signifies that a LtD link is Auto Disabled

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwCubeInserted
item.description: A Cube was inserted

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwCubeRemoved
item.description: A Cube was removed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwStgNewRoot
item.description: A btSwStgNewRoot trap signifies that the bridge has become the new root of the STG

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwCistNewRoot
item.description: A btSwCistNewRoot trap signifies that the bridge has become the new root of the CIST

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwStgTopologyChanged
item.description: A btSwStgTopologyChanged trap signifies that there was a STG topology change

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwCistTopologyChanged
item.description: A btSwCistTopologyChanged trap signifies that there was a CIST topology change

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwHotlinksMasterUp
item.description: A btSwHotlinksMasterUp trap signifies that the Master interface is active

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwHotlinksMasterDn
item.description: A btSwHotlinksMasterDn trap signifies that the Master interface is not active

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwHotlinksBackupUp
item.description: A btSwHotlinksBackupUp trap signifies that the Backup interface is active

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwHotlinksBackupDn
item.description: A btSwHotlinksBackupDn trap signifies that the Backup interface is not active

item.name: Alarm Notification For : bt2SwHotlinksNone
item.description: A btSwHotlinksNone trap signifies that there are no active interfaces

item.name: Alarm Notification For : newRoot
item.description: The newRoot trap indicates that the sending agent has become the new root of the Spanning Tree the trap is sent by a bridge soon after its election as the new root eg upon expiration of the Topology Change Timer immediately subsequent to its election Implementation of this trap is optional

item.name: Alarm Notification For : topologyChange
item.description: A topologyChange trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state The trap is not sent if a newRoot trap is sent for the same transition Implementation of this trap is optional

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaLogDrvStatusChange
item.description: External Array Logical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a External Array logical drive The variable cpqFcaLogDrvStatus indicates the current logical drive status User Action If the logical drive status is failed examine the array for failed drives that need replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaSpareStatusChange
item.description: External Array Spare Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a External Array spare drive The variable cpqFcaSpareStatus indicates the current spare drive status The variable cpqFcaSpareBusNumber indicates the SCSI bus number associated with this drive User Action If the spare drive status is failed replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaPhyDrvStatusChange
item.description: External Array Physical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a physical drive The variable cpaFcaPhyDrvStatus indicates the current physical drive status The variable cpqFcaPhyDrvBusNumber indicates the SCSI bus number associated with this drive User Action If the physical drive status is threshExceeded() predictiveFailure() or failed() replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaAccelStatusChange
item.description: External Array Accelerator Board Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the cpqFcaAccelStatus of a Array Accelerator Cache Board The current status is represented by the variable cpqFcaAccelStatus User Action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaAccelBadDataTrap
item.description: External Array Accelerator Board Bad Data This trap signifies that the agent has detected a Array Accelerator Cache Board that has lost battery power If data was being stored in the accelerator memory when the system lost power that data has been lost User Action Verify that no data has been lost

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaAccelBatteryFailed
item.description: External Array Accelerator Board Battery Failed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a battery failure associated with the Array Accelerator Cache Board User Action Replace the Accelerator Cache Board

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaCntlrStatusChange
item.description: External Array Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a External Array Controller The variable cpqFcaCntlrStatus indicates the current controller status User Action If the controller status is offline access to the storage box has been lost Check the storage box and all fibre channel connections for problems

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcTapeCntlrStatusChange
item.description: Fibre Channel Tape Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a Fiber Channel Tape Controller The variable cpqFcTapeCntlrStatus indicates the current tape controller status The variable cpqFcTapeCntlrWWN indicates the unique tape controller world wide name associated with this controller User Action If the tape controller status is offline access to the tape library and tapes has been lost Check the tape library and all Fibre connections for problems

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcTapeLibraryStatusChange
item.description: Fibre Channel Tape Library Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a Fiber Channel Tape library The variable cpqFcTapeLibraryStatus indicates the current tape library status The variable cpqFcTapeLibraryScsiTarget indicates the SCSI ID of the tape library User Action If the tape library is failed or offline check the tape library front panel and all fibre channel connections

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcTapeLibraryDoorStatusChange
item.description: Fibre Channel Tape Library Door Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the door status of a Fiber Channel Tape library The variable cpqFcTapeLibraryDoorStatus indicates the current tape library door status The variable cpqFcTapeLibraryScsiTarget indicates the the SCSI ID of the tape library User Action If the tape library door is open close the tape library door

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcTapeDriveStatusChange
item.description: Fibre Channel Tape Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a Fiber Channel Tape Drive The variable cpqFcTapeDriveStatus indicates the current tape status The variable cpqFcTapeDriveScsiTarget indicates the the SCSI ID of the tape drive User Action If the tape is failed or offline check the tape and all fibre channel connections

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcTapeDriveCleaningRequired
item.description: Fibre Channel Tape Drive Cleaning Required trap The agent has detected a tape drive that needs to have a cleaning tape inserted and run This will cause the tape drive heads to be cleaned

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcTapeDriveCleanTapeReplace
item.description: Fibre Channel Tape Drive Cleaning Tape Needs Replacing The agent has detected that an autoloader tape unit has a cleaning tape that has been fully used and therefore needs to be replaced with a new cleaning tape

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaCntlrActive
item.description: External Array Redundant Controller Active This trap signifies that the Storage Agent has detected that a backup array controller in a duplexed pair has switched over to the active role The variable cpqFcaCntlrBoxIoSlot indicates the new active controller index User Action Check the partner controller for problems If this was the result of a user initiated switch over no action is required

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFcaHostCntlrStatusChange
item.description: Fibre Channel Host Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the Insight Agent has detected a change in the status of a Fibre Channel Host Controller The variable cpqFcaHostCntlrStatus indicates the current controller status User Action If the controller status is failed replace the controller

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFca2PhyDrvStatusChange
item.description: External Array Physical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a physical drive The variable cpaFcaPhyDrvStatus indicates the current physical drive status User Action If the physical drive status is threshExceeded() predictiveFailure() failed() or unsupportedDrive() replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFca2AccelStatusChange
item.description: External Array Accelerator Board Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a Array Accelerator Cache Board The current status is represented by the variable cpqFcaAccelStatus User Action If the accelerator board status is permDisabled() you may need to replace the accelerator board

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFca2AccelBadDataTrap
item.description: External Array Accelerator Board Bad Data This trap signifies that the agent has detected a Array Accelerator Cache Board that has lost battery power If data was being stored in the accelerator memory when the system lost power that data has been lost User Action Verify that no data has been lost

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFca2AccelBatteryFailed
item.description: External Array Accelerator Board Battery Failed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a battery failure associated with the Array Accelerator Cache Board User Action Replace the Accelerator Cache Board

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFca2CntlrStatusChange
item.description: External Array Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a External Array Controller The variable cpqFcaCntlrStatus indicates the current controller status User Action If the controller status is offline() access to the storage box has been lost Check the storage box and all fibre channel connections for problems

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFca2HostCntlrStatusChange
item.description: Fibre Channel Host Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a Fibre Channel Host Controller The variable cpqFcaHostCntlrStatus indicates the current controller status User Action If the controller status is failed replace the controller

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqExtArrayLogDrvStatusChange
item.description: External Array Logical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of an External Array logical drive The variable cpqFcaLogDrvStatus indicates the current logical drive status User Action If the logical drive status is failed examine the array for failed drives that need replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqExtTapeDriveStatusChange
item.description: External Tape Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of an External Tape Drive The variable cpqFcTapeDriveStatus indicates the current tape status User Action If the tape is failed or offline check the tape and all connections

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqExtTapeDriveCleaningRequired
item.description: External Tape Drive Cleaning Required The agent has detected a tape drive that needs to have a cleaning tape inserted and run This will cause the tape drive heads to be cleaned

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqExtTapeDriveCleanTapeReplace
item.description: External Tape Drive Cleaning Tape Needs Replacing The agent has detected that an autoloader tape unit has a cleaning tape that has been fully used and therefore needs to be replaced with a new cleaning tape

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqExtTapeLibraryStatusChange
item.description: External Tape Library Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of an External Tape library The variable cpqFcTapeLibraryStatus indicates the current tape library status User Action If the tape library is failed or offline check the tape library front panel and all connections

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqExtTapeLibraryDoorStatusChange
item.description: External Tape Library Door Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the door status of an External Tape library The variable cpqFcTapeLibraryDoorStatus indicates the current tape library door status User Action If the tape library door is open close the tape library door

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqFca3HostCntlrStatusChange
item.description: Fibre Channel Host Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a Fibre Channel Host Controller The variable cpqFcaHostCntlrStatus indicates the current controller status User Action If the controller status is failed replace the controller

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeCorrectableMemoryError
item.description: A correctable memory error occurred The error has been corrected The current number of correctable memory errors is reported in the variable cpqHeCorrMemTotalErrs

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeCorrectableMemoryLogDisabled
item.description: Correctable memory error tracking disabled The frequency of errors is so high that the error tracking logic has been temporarily disabled The cpqHeCorrMemLogStatus variable indicated the current tracking status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe2CorrectableMemoryError
item.description: A correctable memory error occurred The error has been corrected The current number of correctable memory errors is reported in the variable cpqHeCorrMemTotalErrs

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe2CorrectableMemoryLogDisabled
item.description: Correctable memory error tracking disabled The frequency of errors is so high that the error tracking logic has been temporarily disabled The cpqHeCorrMemLogStatus variable indicated the current tracking status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalTempFailed
item.description: The temperature status has been set to failed The system will be shutdown due to this thermal condition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalTempDegraded
item.description: The temperature status has been set to degraded The server's temperature is outside of the normal operating range The server will be shutdown if the cpqHeThermalDegradedAction variable is set to shutdown()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalTempOk
item.description: The temperature status has been set to ok The server's temperature has returned to the normal operating range

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalSystemFanFailed
item.description: The system fan status has been set to failed A required system fan is not operating normally The system will be shutdown if the cpqHeThermalDegradedAction variable is set to shutdown()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalSystemFanDegraded
item.description: The system fan status has been set to degraded An optional system fan is not operating normally

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalSystemFanOk
item.description: The system fan status has been set to ok Any previously nonoperational system fans have returned to normal operation

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalCpuFanFailed
item.description: The CPU fan status has been set to failed A processor fan is not operating normally The server will be shutdown

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalCpuFanOk
item.description: The CPU fan status has been set to ok Any previously nonoperational processor fans have returned to normal operation

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeAsrConfirmation
item.description: The server is operational again The server has previously been shutdown by the Automatic Server Recovery (ASR) feature and has just become operational again

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeThermalConfirmation
item.description: The server is operational again The server has previously been shutdown due to a thermal anomaly on the server and has just become operational again

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHePostError
item.description: One or more POST errors occurred Power On SelfTest (POST) errors occur during the server restart process

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeFltTolPwrSupplyDegraded
item.description: The fault tolerant power supply subsystem condition has been set to degraded

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3CorrectableMemoryError

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3CorrectableMemoryLogDisabled
item.description: Correctable memory error tracking disabled The frequency of errors is so high that the error tracking logic has been temporarily disabled The cpqHeCorrMemLogStatus variable indicated the current tracking status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3ThermalTempFailed
item.description: The temperature status has been set to failed The system will be shutdown due to this thermal condition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3ThermalTempDegraded
item.description: The temperature status has been set to degraded The server's temperature is outside of the normal operating range The server will be shutdown if the cpqHeThermalDegradedAction variable is set to shutdown()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3ThermalTempOk
item.description: The temperature status has been set to ok The server's temperature has returned to the normal operating range

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3ThermalSystemFanFailed
item.description: The system fan status has been set to failed A required system fan is not operating normally The system will be shutdown if the cpqHeThermalDegradedAction variable is set to shutdown()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3ThermalSystemFanDegraded
item.description: The system fan status has been set to degraded An optional system fan is not operating normally

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3ThermalSystemFanOk
item.description: The system fan status has been set to ok Any previously nonoperational system fans have returned to normal operation

item.description: The CPU fan status has been set to failed A processor fan is not operating normally The server will be shutdown

item.description: The CPU fan status has been set to ok Any previously nonoperational processor fans have returned to normal operation

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3AsrConfirmation
item.description: The server is operational again The server has previously been shutdown by the Automatic Server Recovery (ASR) feature and has just become operational again

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3ThermalConfirmation
item.description: The server is operational again The server has previously been shutdown due to a thermal anomaly on the server and has just become operational again

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3PostError
item.description: One or more POST errors occurred Power On SelfTest (POST) errors occur during the server restart process Details of the POST error messages can be found in Integrated Management Log

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolPwrSupplyDegraded
item.description: The fault tolerant power supply subsystem condition has been set to degraded

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3CorrMemReplaceMemModule
item.description: A correctable memory log entry indicates a memory module needs to be replaced The errors have been corrected but the memory module should be replaced The error Minor is reported in the variable cpqHeCorrMemErrDesc

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolPowerSupplyDegraded
item.description: The fault tolerant power supply condition has been set to degraded for the specified chassis and bay location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolPowerSupplyFailed
item.description: The fault tolerant power supply condition has been set to failed for the specified chassis and bay location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolPowerRedundancyLost
item.description: The Fault Tolerant Power Supplies have lost redundancy for the specified chassis

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolPowerSupplyInserted
item.description: A Fault Tolerant Power Supply has been inserted into the specified chassis and bay location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolPowerSupplyRemoved
item.description: A Fault Tolerant Power Supply has been removed from the specified chassis and bay location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolFanDegraded
item.description: The Fault Tolerant Fan condition has been set to degraded for the specified chassis and fan

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolFanFailed
item.description: The Fault Tolerant Fan condition has been set to failed for the specified chassis and fan

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolFanRedundancyLost
item.description: The Fault Tolerant Fans have lost redundancy for the specified chassis

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolFanInserted
item.description: A Fault Tolerant Fan has been inserted into the specified chassis and fan location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolFanRemoved

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3TemperatureFailed
item.description: The temperature status has been set to failed in the specified chassis and location The system will be shutdown due to this condition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3TemperatureDegraded
item.description: The temperature status has been set to degraded in the specified chassis and location The server's temperature is outside of the normal operating range The server will be shutdown if the cpqHeThermalDegradedAction variable is set to shutdown()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3TemperatureOk
item.description: The temperature status has been set to ok in the specified chassis and location The server's temperature has returned to the normal operating range

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3PowerConverterDegraded
item.description: The DCDC Power Converter condition has been set to degraded for the specified chassis slot and socket

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3PowerConverterFailed
item.description: The DCDC Power Converter condition has been set to failed for the specified chassis slot and socket

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3PowerConverterRedundancyLost
item.description: The DCDC Power Converters have lost redundancy for the specified chassis

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3CacheAccelParityError
item.description: A cache accelerator parity error indicates a cache module needs to be replaced The error Minor is reported in the variable cpqHeEventLogErrorDesc

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeResilientMemOnlineSpareEngaged
item.description: Advanced Memory Protection Online Spare Engaged The Advanced Memory Protection subsystem has detected a memory fault The Online Spare Memory has been activated User Action Schedule server downtime to replace the faulty memory

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe4FltTolPowerSupplyOk
item.description: The fault tolerant power supply condition has been set back to the OK state for the specified chassis and bay location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe4FltTolPowerSupplyDegraded
item.description: The fault tolerant power supply condition has been set to degraded for the specified chassis and bay location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe4FltTolPowerSupplyFailed
item.description: The fault tolerant power supply condition has been set to failed for the specified chassis and bay location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeResilientMemMirroredMemoryEngaged
item.description: Advanced Memory Protection Mirrored Memory Engaged The Advanced Memory Protection subsystem has detected a memory fault Mirrored Memory has been activated User Action Replace the faulty memory

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeResilientAdvancedECCMemoryEngaged
item.description: Advanced Memory Protection Advanced ECC Memory Engaged The Advanced Memory Protection subsystem has detected a memory fault Advanced ECC has been activated User Action Replace the faulty memory

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeResilientMemXorMemoryEngaged
item.description: Advanced Memory Protection XOR Engine Memory Engaged The Advanced Memory Protection subsystem has detected a memory fault The XOR engine has been activated User Action Replace the faulty memory

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolPowerRedundancyRestored
item.description: The Fault Tolerant Power Supplies have returned to a redundant state for the specified chassis

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe3FltTolFanRedundancyRestored
item.description: The Fault Tolerant Fans have returned to a redundant state for the specified chassis

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe4CorrMemReplaceMemModule
item.description: Corrected Memory Errors Detected The errors have been corrected but the memory module should be replaced

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeResMemBoardRemoved
item.description: Memory board or cartridge removed An Advanced Memory Protection subsystem board or cartridge has been removed from the system User Action Insure the board or cartridge has memory correctly installed and reinsert the memory board or cartridge back into the system

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeResMemBoardInserted
item.description: Memory board or cartridge inserted An Advanced Memory Protection subsystem board or cartridge has been inserted into the system User Action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeResMemBoardBusError
item.description: Memory board or cartridge bus error detected An Advanced Memory Protection subsystem board or cartridge bus error has been detected User Action Replace the indicated board or cartridge

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeEventOccurred
item.description: An event has occurred User Action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeManagementProcInReset
item.description: The Management processor is currently in reset The management processor is currently in the process of being reset because of a firmware update or some other event User action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeManagementProcReady
item.description: The Management processor is ready The management processor has successfully reset and is now available again User action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeManagementProcFailedReset
item.description: The Management processor failed reset The management processor was not successfully reset and is not operational User action Reset the management procesessor again or reflash the management processor firmware

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe5CorrMemReplaceMemModule
item.description: Corrected \ uncorrected Memory Errors Detected The errors have been corrected but the memory module should be replaced Value for CPU means memory is not Processor based

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe5ResMemBoardRemoved
item.description: Memory board or cartridge or riser removed An Advanced Memory Protection subsystem board or cartridge or riser has been removed from the system Value for CPU means memory is not processor based User Action Insure the board or cartridge or riser has memory correctly installed and reinsert the memory board or cartridge or CPU back into the system

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe5ResMemBoardInserted
item.description: Memory board or cartridge or riser inserted An Advanced Memory Protection subsystem board or cartridge or riser Has been inserted into the system Value for CPU means memory is not processor based User Action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe5ResMemBoardBusError
item.description: Memory board or cartridge or Riser bus error detected An Advanced Memory Protection subsystem board or cartridge or Riser bus error has been detected Value for CPU means memory is not processor based User Action Replace the indicated board or cartridge or Riser

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHeResilientMemLockStepMemoryEngaged
item.description: Advanced Memory Protection LockStep Engine Memory Engaged The Advanced Memory Protection subsystem has detected a memory fault The LockStep engine has been activated User Action Replace the faulty memory

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHe4FltTolPowerSupplyACpowerloss
item.description: The fault tolerant power supply AC power loss for the specified chassis and bay location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHoGenericTrap
item.description: Generic trap

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHoAppErrorTrap
item.description: An application has generated an exception Specific error Minor is contained in the variable cpqHoSwPerfAppErrorDesc

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHo2GenericTrap
item.description: Generic trap

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHo2AppErrorTrap
item.description: An application has generated an exception Specific error Minor is contained in the variable cpqHoSwPerfAppErrorDesc

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHo2NicStatusOk
item.description: This trap will be sent any time the status of a NIC changes to the OK condition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHo2NicStatusFailed
item.description: This trap will be sent any time the status of a NIC changes to the Failed condition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqHo2NicSwitchoverOccurred
item.description: This trap will be sent any time the configured redundant NIC becomes the active NIC

item.description: Accelerator Board Battery Failed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a battery failure associated with the array accelerator cache board The current battery status is indicated by the cpqDaAccelBattery variable

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa3LogDrvStatusChange
item.description: Logical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array logical drive The variable cpqDaLogDrvStatus indicates the current logical drive status

item.description: Spare Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array spare drive The variable cpqDaSpareStatus indicates the current spare drive status The variable cpqDaSpareBusNumber indicates the SCSI bus number associated with this drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa3PhyDrvStatusChange

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa3AccelStatusChange
item.description: Accelerator Board Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the cpqDaAccelStatus of an array accelerator cache board The current status is represented by the variable cpqDaAccelStatus

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa3AccelBadDataTrap
item.description: Accelerator Board Bad Data This trap signifies that the agent has detected an array accelerator cache board that has lost battery power If data was being stored in the accelerator memory when the server lost power that data has been lost

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa3AccelBatteryFailed
item.description: Accelerator Board Battery Failed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a battery failure associated with the array accelerator cache board The current battery status is indicated by the cpqDaAccelBattery variable

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaCntlrStatusChange
item.description: Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array controller The variable cpqDaCntlrBoardStatus indicates the current controller status User Action If the board status is generalFailure() the you may need to replace the controller If the board status is cableProblem() check the cable connections between the controller and the storage system

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaCntlrActive
item.description: Controller Active This trap signifies that the agent has detected that a backup array controller in a duplexed pair has switched over to the active role The variable cpqDaCntlrSlot indicates the active controller slot and cpqDaCntlrPartnerSlot indicates the backup User Action Check the partner controller for problems If this was the result of a user initiated switch over no action is required

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa4SpareStatusChange
item.description: Spare Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array spare drive The variable cpqDaSpareStatus indicates the current spare drive status User Action If the spare drive status is failed replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa4PhyDrvStatusChange
item.description: Physical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array physical drive The variable cpaDaPhyDrvStatus indicates the current physical drive status User Action If the physical drive failed or predicting failure replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa4PhyDrvThreshPassedTrap
item.description: Physical Drive Threshold Passed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a factory threshold associated with one of the physical drive objects on a drive array has been exceeded User Action If the physical drive is predicting failure replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaTapeLibraryStatusChange
item.description: Tape Library Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a tape library The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryStatus indicates the current tape library status The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryScsiTarget indicates the SCSI ID of the tape library User Action If the tape library is failed check the tape library front panel

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaTapeLibraryDoorStatusChange
item.description: Tape Library Door Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the door status of a tape library The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryDoorStatus indicates the current tape library door status The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryScsiTarget indicates the the SCSI ID of the tape library User Action If the tape library door is open close the tape library door

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaTapeDriveStatusChange
item.description: Tape Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a tape drive The variable cpqDaTapeDrvStatus indicates the current tape status The variable cpqDaTapeDrvScsiIdIndex indicates the the SCSI ID of the tape drive User Action If the tape is failed check the tape and all SCSI connections

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaTapeDriveCleaningRequired
item.description: Tape Drive Cleaning Required trap The agent has detected a tape drive that needs to have a cleaning tape inserted and run This will cause the tape drive heads to be cleaned

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaTapeDriveCleanTapeReplace
item.description: Tape Drive Cleaning Tape Needs Replacing The agent has detected that an autoloader tape unit has a cleaning tape that has been fully used and therefore needs to be replaced with a new cleaning tape

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa5AccelStatusChange
item.description: Accelerator Board Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of an array accelerator cache board The current status is represented by the variable cpqDaAccelStatus User Action If the accelerator board status is permDisabled() you may need to replace the accelerator board

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa5AccelBadDataTrap
item.description: Accelerator Board Bad Data This trap signifies that the agent has detected an array accelerator cache board that has lost battery power If data was being stored in the accelerator cache memory when the server lost power that data has been lost User Action Verify that no data has been lost

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa5AccelBatteryFailed
item.description: Accelerator Board Battery Failed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a battery failure associated with the array accelerator cache board User Action Replace the Accelerator Cache Board

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa5CntlrStatusChange
item.description: Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array controller The variable cpqDaCntlrBoardStatus indicates the current controller status User Action If the board status is generalFailure() you may need to replace the controller If the board status is cableProblem() check the cable connections between the controller and the storage system

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa5PhyDrvStatusChange
item.description: Physical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array physical drive The variable cpaDaPhyDrvStatus indicates the current physical drive status User Action If the physical drive status is failed() or predictiveFailure() replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa5PhyDrvThreshPassedTrap
item.description: Physical Drive Threshold Passed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a factory threshold associated with one of the physical drive objects on a drive array has been exceeded User Action Replace the physical drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa2TapeLibraryStatusChange
item.description: Tape Library Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a tape library The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryStatus indicates the current tape library status The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryScsiTarget indicates the SCSI ID of the tape library User Action If the tape library is failed check the tape library front panel

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa2TapeDriveStatusChange
item.description: Tape Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a tape drive The variable cpqDaTapeDrvStatus indicates the current tape status The variable cpqDaTapeDrvScsiIdIndex indicates the the SCSI ID of the tape drive User Action If the tape is failed check the tape and all SCSI connections

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6CntlrStatusChange
item.description: Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array controller The variable cpqDaCntlrBoardStatus indicates the current controller status User Action If cpqDaCntlrBoardStatus is 'generalFailure()' you may need to reboot the server or replace the controller After the system is rebooted check the variable cpqDaCntlrLastLockupCode for the controller?s last lockup code If cpqDaCntlrBoardStatus is 'cableProblem()' check the cable connections between the controller and the storage system If cpqDaCntlrBoardStatus is 'cacheModuleMissing()' the array controller is operating in an unsupported configuration and requires that a cache module be attached to the controller

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6LogDrvStatusChange
item.description: Logical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array logical drive The variable cpqDaLogDrvStatus indicates the current logical drive status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6SpareStatusChange
item.description: Spare Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array spare drive The variable cpqDaSpareStatus indicates the current spare drive status User Action If the spare drive status is failed replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6PhyDrvStatusChange
item.description: Physical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array physical drive The variable cpaDaPhyDrvStatus indicates the current physical drive status User Action If the physical drive status is failed() or predictiveFailure() replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6PhyDrvThreshPassedTrap
item.description: Physical Drive Threshold Passed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a factory threshold associated with one of the physical drive objects on a drive array has been exceeded User Action Replace the physical drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6AccelStatusChange
item.description: Cache Module Board Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a cache module board The current status is represented by the variable cpqDaAccelStatus User Action If cpqDaAccelStatus is 'permDisabled()' you may need to replace the cache module board If cpqDaAccelStatus is 'cacheModFlashMemNotAttached()' install the flash memory

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6AccelBadDataTrap
item.description: Cache Module Board Bad Data This trap signifies that the agent has detected a cache module board that has lost backup power If data was being stored in the cache module memory when the server lost power that data has been lost The backup power source is indicated by cpqDaAccelBackupPowerSource User Action Verify that no data has been lost

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6AccelBatteryFailed
item.description: Cache Module Board Backup Power Source Failed This trap signifies that the agent has detected a backup power source failure associated with the cache module board The backup power source is indicated by cpqDaAccelBackupPowerSource User Action Replace the Backup Power Source

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6TapeLibraryStatusChange
item.description: Tape Library Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a tape library The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryStatus indicates the current tape library status The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryScsiTarget indicates the SCSI ID of the tape library User Action If cpqDaTapeLibraryStatus is 'failed()' check the tape library front panel

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6TapeLibraryDoorStatusChange
item.description: Tape Library Door Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the door status of a tape library The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryDoorStatus indicates the current tape library door status The variable cpqDaTapeLibraryScsiTarget indicates the the SCSI ID of the tape library User Action If cpqDaTapeLibraryDoorStatus is 'open()' close the tape library door

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6TapeDriveStatusChange
item.description: Tape Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a tape drive The variable cpqDaTapeDrvStatus indicates the current tape status The variable cpqDaTapeDrvScsiIdIndex indicates the the SCSI ID of the tape drive User Action If cpqDaTapeDrvStatus is 'failed()' check the tape and all SCSI connections

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6TapeDriveCleaningRequired
item.description: Tape Drive Cleaning Required trap The agent has detected a tape drive that needs to have a cleaning tape inserted and run This will cause the tape drive heads to be cleaned

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa6TapeDriveCleanTapeReplace
item.description: Tape Drive Cleaning Tape Needs Replacing The agent has detected that an autoloader tape unit has a cleaning tape that has been fully used and therefore needs to be replaced with a new cleaning tape

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa7PhyDrvStatusChange
item.description: Physical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array physical drive The variable cpaDaPhyDrvStatus indicates the current physical drive status User Action If cpaDaPhyDrvStatus is 'failed()' 'predictiveFailure()' 'ssdWearOut()' or 'notAuthenticated()' replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDa7SpareStatusChange
item.description: Spare Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array spare drive The variable cpqDaSpareStatus indicates the current spare drive status User Action If cpqDaSpareStatus is 'failed()' replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaCntlrPartnerStatusChange
item.description: Partner Controller Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of a drive array partner controller The variable cpqDaCntlrPartnerBoardStatus indicates the current partner controller status The variable cpqDaCntlrSerialNumber indicates the controller?s serial number and cpqDaCntlrPartnerSerialNumber indicates the partner controller?s serial number User Action Check the partner controller for problems If lost communication with the partner controller is the result of a user initiated action no remedial action is required

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaPhyDrvSSDWearStatusChange
item.description: Solid State Disk Wear Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the SSD wear status of a drive array physical drive The variable cpqDaPhyDrvSSDWearStatus indicates the current SSD wear status User Action If cpqDaPhyDrvSSDWearStatus is 'ssdWearOut()' replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaSasLinkDown
item.description: SAS Link Down This trap signifies that the agent has detected a SAS link has gone down The variable cpqDaDaCntlrHwLocation indicates the location of the controller on which the change was detected User Action Check the cables and connectors on all paths to all connected drives

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqDaSasLinkUp
item.description: SAS Link Up This trap signifies that the agent has detected a SAS link is up The variable cpqDaDaCntlrHwLocation indicates the location of the controller on which the change was detected User Action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqIdeDriveDegraded
item.description: An IDE drive status has been set to degraded User Action The drive should be scheduled for replacement Refer to the appropriate Maintenance and Service Guide for detailed Minor on a component replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqIdeDriveOk
item.description: An IDE drive status has been set to ok User Action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqIdeDriveUltraAtaDegraded
item.description: An IDE drive detects an excessive number of Ultra ATA data transmission errors between the hard drive and the processor User Action For best performance move Ultra ATA devices to the primary controller and non Ultra ATA devices to the secondary controller If errors still persist consider replacing the standard conductor IDE cable with an conductor Ultra ATA cable

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqIdeAtaDiskStatusChange
item.description: ATA Disk Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of an ATA disk drive The variable cpqIdeAtaDiskStatus indicates the current disk drive status User Action If cpqIdeAtaDiskStatus is 'smartError()' 'failed()' or 'ssdWearOut()' replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqIdeLogicalDriveStatusChange
item.description: IDE Logical Drive Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the status of an IDE logical drive The variable cpqIdeLogicalDriveStatus indicates the current logical drive status User Action If the logical drive status is failed() examine the array for failed drives that need replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqIdeAtaDiskSSDWearStatusChange
item.description: Solid State Disk Wear Status Change This trap signifies that the agent has detected a change in the SSD wear status of a SATA physical drive The variable cpqIdeAtaDiskSSDWearStatus indicates the current SSD wear status User Action If cpqIdeAtaDiskSSDWearStatus is 'ssdWearOut()' replace the drive

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqNicConnectivityRestored
item.description: This trap will be sent any time connectivity is restored to a logical adapter This occurs when the physical adapter in a single adapter configuration returns to the OK condition or at least one physical adapter in a logical adapter group returns to the OK condition This can be caused by replacement of a faulty cable or reattaching a cable that was unplugged User Action None required

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqNicConnectivityLost
item.description: This trap will be sent any time the status of a logical adapter changes to the Failed condition This occurs when the adapter in a single adapter configuration fails or when the last adapter in a redundant configuration fails This can be caused by loss of link due to a cable being removed from the adapter or the Hub or Switch Internal adapter Hub or Switch failures can also cause this condition User Action Check the cables to the adapter and the Hub or Switch If no cable problems are found the adapter Hub or Switch may need replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqNicRedundancyIncreased
item.description: This trap will be sent any time a previously failed physical adapter in a connected logical adapter group returns to the OK condition This trap is not sent when a logical adapter group has connectivity restored from a Failed condition The cpqNicConnectivityRestored trap is sent instead This can be caused by replacement of a faulty cable or reattaching a cable that was unplugged User Action None required

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqNicRedundancyReduced
item.description: This trap will be sent any time a physical adapter in a logical adapter group changes to the Failed condition but at least one physical adapter remains in the OK condition This can be caused by loss of link due to a cable being removed from the adapter or the Hub or Switch Internal adapter Hub or Switch failures can also cause this condition User Action Check the cables to the adapter and the Hub or Switch If no cable problems are found the adapter Hub or Switch may need replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqNic2ConnectivityRestored

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqNic2ConnectivityLost
item.description: This trap will be sent any time the status of a logical adapter changes to the Failed condition This occurs when the adapter in a single adapter configuration fails or when the last adapter in a redundant configuration fails This can be caused by loss of link due to a cable being removed from the adapter or the Hub or Switch Internal adapter Hub or Switch failures can also cause this condition User Action Check the cables to the adapter and the Hub or Switch If no cable problems are found the adapter Hub or Switch may need replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqNic2RedundancyReduced
item.description: This trap will be sent any time a physical adapter in a logical adapter group changes to the Failed condition but at least one physical adapter remains in the OK condition This can be caused by loss of link due to a cable being removed from the adapter or the Hub or Switch Internal adapter Hub or Switch failures can also cause this condition User Action Check the cables to the adapter and the Hub or Switch If no cable problems are found the adapter Hub or Switch may need replacement

item.description: This trap will be sent when the Virus Throttle Filter Driver detects virus like activity User Action The system reporting this trap requires immediate attention

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqNicVirusLikeActivityStopped
item.description: This trap will be sent when the Virus Throttle Filter Driver no longer detects virus like activity User Action None required

item.description: This trap will be sent any time a previously failed physical adapter in a connected logical adapter group returns to the OK condition This trap is not sent when a logical adapter group has connectivity restored from a Failed condition The cpqNicConnectivityRestored trap is sent instead This can be caused by replacement of a faulty cable or reattaching a cable that was unplugged User Action None required

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqServiceMinor
item.description: This trap will be sent any time a service incident is logged or updated A service incident is generated when it is determined that a service event has occurred based upon an analysis of system initiated event traps or an update to a service event has occurred User Action None Required

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqService2Minor
item.description: This event will be sent any time a service incident is reported A service incident is generated when it is determined that a serviceable event has occurred based upon analysis of systeminitiated events User Action Refer to the Recommended Action section under the event details section

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiHoodRemoved
item.description: System hood is removed The hood status has been set to removed The system's hood is not in a properly installed state This situation may result in improper cooling of the system due to air flow changes caused by the missing hood User Action Replace the cover (hood) ensure the system's cover is properly installed Verify the system is in working order

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiMonitorConditionOK
item.description: Fault reporting features have returned to within their normal operating range for the monitor indicated by cpqSiMonitorIndex The monitor's condition has been set to OK User Action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiMonitorConditionDegraded
item.description: A fault reporting feature has exceeded normal limits for the monitor indicated by the cpqSiMonitorIndex The monitor's condition is degraded due to the internal temperature exceeding normal operating limits The monitor is still useable but action should be taken to return the condition to OK User Action Physically check for obstructions to air flow around the monitor Check the thermostat in the room that the system occupies Allow the monitor to cool by turning off the monitor for minutes then turn the monitor back on After the monitor cools another alarm indicating an improving condition such as Monitor OK will be issued

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiMonitorConditionFailed
item.description: A fault reporting feature has exceeded normal limits in the monitor indicated by the cpqSiMonitorIndex The monitor's condition has been set to failed due to an operational feature exceeding normal operating limits The monitor will not be useable and should be replaced User Action Make a note of the monitor model number and serial number Replace the monitor Refer to the appropriate Maintenance and Service Guide for detailed Minor on a component replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiCorrMemErrStatusDegraded
item.description: Correctable memory error count has exceeded the threshold for the memory module indicated by the 'cpqSiMemErrorIndex' variable The appropriate cpqSiMemModuleECCStatus has been set to degraded User Action For Desktops the System Administrator should run the F Diagnostics on this system and select RAM LONG TEST If it is determined that a module needs replacing schedule maintenance for the system and replace the failed memory module Refer to the appropriate Maintenance and Service Guide for detailed Minor on a component replacement

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiCorrMemErrStatusOk
item.description: Correctable memory error count is now below the threshold for the memory module indicated by the 'cpqSiMemErrorIndex' variable The appropriate cpqSiMemModuleECCStatus has been set to ok User Action None

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiMemConfigChange
item.description: A memory configuration change has occurred CpqSiMemConfigChangeData will indicate which memory modules slots have changed User Action You may want to verify a valid reason for a memory configuration to have occurred If system issuing the alert is a Desktop running NT the memory configuration change Minor is also logged in the NT System Log

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiHotPlugSlotBoardInserted

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiSysBatteryFailure
item.description: The battery indicated by cpqSiSysBatteryIndex has failed and must be replaced User Action Contact your System Administrator or Authorized Reseller to order a replacement battery Recycle your old battery For proper disposal Minor refer to the documentation that came with your computer

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSiSysBatteryChargingDegraded

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSmAlertDestinationBlacklisted
item.description: Alert destination blacklisted The Server Manager board modem has blacklisted an alert destination phone number Once blacklisted that alert destination is no longer available for use as an alert destination Blacklisting which only occurs in international modems is a requirement imposed by certain European countries on modems to prevent a phone number from being dialed multiple times without getting a connection The number of attempts required to have blacklisting occur vary from country to country Once an alert destination has been blacklisted the only way to remove the blacklisted phone number is to remove power from the modem On external modems this is a trival task When a blacklisting occurs on the Server Manager board's internal modem the task is slightly more difficult as the modem gets power from the Server Manager board To remove power from the Server Manager board's internal modem the Server Manager board must be forced into Dormant Mode This is an operating mode used to conserve battery life which is entered automatically if the board looses power To cause the board to enter Dormant Mode the following steps should be performed ) Disable alerting via CPQCAUINLM ) Disable async communication via CPQCAUINLM ) Down the server ) Exit to DOS (if applicable) ) Shut power off to the computer ) Wait minutes before restoring power Once the minutes has expired and power to the computer has been restored the modem will have flushed its blacklist and the board's alerting functions will work as expected

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSeCpuThresholdPassed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSePCCardThermalDegraded
item.description: This trap is sent when the PC Card Slot Thermal Sensor threshold has been exceeded for safe operations thereby causing degraded operations This trap will be sent when cpqSePCCardStatus transitions from Normal () to Thermal Degraded () The manufacturer and product Minor strings as well as the slot number for the degraded PC Card is provided as parameters for this trap

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSePCCardThermalFailure
item.description: This trap is sent when the PC Card Slot Thermal Sensor threshold has been exceeded for degraded operations thereby causing failed operations This trap will be sent when cpqSePCCardStatus transitions from Thermal Degraded () to Thermal Failure () The manufacturer and product Minor strings as well as the slot number for the failed PC Card is provided as parameters for this trap

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSePCCardThermalSafe
item.description: This trap is sent when the PC Card Slot Thermal Sensor threshold has been crossed which restored the thermal status to normal operations This trap will be sent when cpqSePCCardStatus transitions from Thermal Degraded () or Thermal Failure () to Normal () The number of the recovered PC Card slot is provided as a parameter for this trap

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpqSe2CpuThresholdPassed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemEccSbeEccTstFailed
