item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSalFreqBaseUnknown
item.description: While attempting to calibrate the EFI stall timer system firmware is unable to determine the frequency of the CPU interval timer System firmware will assume MHz for the purpose of the stall timer calibration and continue boot Data Field error status code (should be xFFFFFFFD)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSysEventAlreadyInit
item.description: The EFI system events have already been initialized This is unexpected EFI is continuing Data Field the current value of the system event entry point

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSysEventCreateEventFail
item.description: EFI was unable to create an internal virtualization event while initializing EFI's System Events (IPMI events) This internal event is not an IPMI event rather it serves as a trigger for EFI to virtualize the System Event facility when going virtual EFI will likely halt Data Field return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFpgaNodeInitError
item.description: An error was detected while initializing the FPGA node and services associated with the PDH

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIoconfigNodeInitError
item.description: Firmware encountered an error when creating the ioconfig node as a child of the pdh node

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtDillonPdhNodeInitError
item.description: System firmware was unable to correctly set up the pdh arbiter node as a child of the pdh node or was unable to locate and attach the pdh arbiter service to the node The status is returned in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhPropertyError
item.description: The PDH service was unable to either get or set the property specified in the data field as an ASCII message

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhAcpihwNodeError
item.description: PDH encountered an error creating the ACPI Hardware Node in the device tree or installing its properties

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhIpmiNodeError
item.description: The PDH service encountered an error while creating the ipmi node or adding properties to it The status is in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCpusNotCompatible
item.description: Installed processors are not of compatible models or families

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCacheSizesInconsistant
item.description: Processors with different cache sizes are installed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootSelectingNewMonarch
item.description: SFW is selecting a new monarch processor due to compatibility problems

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMonSelSteppingsNoEqual
item.description: The monarch stepping is not equal to the lowest installed CPU stepping

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCpuOverClocked
item.description: A CPU's FSB frequency is overclocked Data Local CPU Number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCpuInfoRomAccessError
item.description: There was an error reading the info ROM area of the CPU Data CPU Physical location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootPalANotExecuted
item.description: PAL_A has not been executed and control has been transferred back to SAL_B

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootPalBNotExecuted
item.description: PAL_B has not been executed and control has been transferred back to SAL_B

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootProtoTypeCpuInstalled
item.description: Data Lower bits have Local CPU Number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootFinalRendezWatchdogFail
item.description: Data Monarch's Local CPU Number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuSupplementalTestFailed
item.description: Supplemental tests have been run on the cpus in the node and an error was encountered If this event id is only emitted once then the cpu detected that it failed on its own and the offending CPU id is in the data field If the event is emitted three times then the monarch CPU on the cell detected the error and the offending CPU id expected data and actual data are reported in the data field of the three events

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricReadMbeError
item.description: While reading a XBC CSR a multibit error was found Data field includes the CSR data that includes the error A previous event FABRIC_READ_ERROR details the CSR address that failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricUnexpectedStatus
item.description: The return value from a function was an unknown value Data field is the unknown status that was returned

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSysidBmcWarning
item.description: EFI queries the BMC on the system board for the status of a system ID The BMC could not complete the request successfully or on time Data Field Internal EFI function status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSysidBmcReadError
item.description: BMC reported a system ID status as inaccessible reported invalid status or cannot return the current value of a system ID Data Field uuid status or internal EFI function status System ID status a byte value extended to bits x > primary and secondary values are valid x > primary and secondary values are magic x > primary and secondary values are inaccessible x > primary and secondary values are invalid x > primary and secondary values are null (UUID only) x > primary and secondary values are different value (primary or secondary) is valid x > primary and secondary values are different value (primary or secondary) is magic x > primary and secondary values are different value (primary or secondary) is inaccessible x > primary and secondary values are different value (primary or secondary) is invalid x > primary and secondary values are different value (primary or secondary) is null (UUID only)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSysidBmcWriteError
item.description: Firmware tried to write a primary or secondary system ID as requested by the user during the boot sequence The write failed Data Field Internal EFI function status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSysidInvalid
item.description: The system ID(s) currently in the system is either invalid or if the EFI_SYSID_BMC_WARNING EFI_SYSID_BMC_READ_ERROR or EFI_SYSID_BMC_WRITE_ERROR events are also present inaccessible to the system firmware A stop boot condition will be generated and software license will probably be invalid Data Field bit value If preceded by xbad the following valid values are possible > valid UUID (should never see this one) > magic UUID > inaccessible UUID > invalid (bad CRC) UUID If zero then one of the following conditions occurred Invalid combination of primary and secondary system ID values User declined copyingentering system ID values when prompted by firmware All other values indicate failure during attempt to update system IDs

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiRtIvtEsiTableErr
item.description: EFI is unable to find the SAL services for installing interrupt handlers EFI was trying to install the runtime handlers that are required for normal EFI booting EFI will be halting Data Field internal EFI function status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiRtIvtEsiQueryErr
item.description: EFI is unable to find the SAL service to install runtime interrupt handlers These handlers are required for normal EFI booting EFI will be halting Data Field internal EFI function status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiBootIvtEsiTableErr
item.description: EFI is unable to find the SAL services for installing interrupt handlers EFI was trying to install the boottime handlers that are required for normal EFI booting EFI will be halting Data Field internal EFI function status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiBootIvtEsiQueryErr
item.description: EFI is unable to find the SAL service to install boottime interrupt handlers These handlers are required for normal EFI booting EFI will be halting Data Field internal EFI function status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtUtilitiesParmListTooLarge
item.description: Too many parameters were passed in a request for the utilities system to perform an operation No more data is provided

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortPresenceError
item.description: A crossbar port is expected to be present but its presence detect bit is not set Data field bits contain the crossbar ID bits contain the port number for which the error occurred and bits contain the port status Minor

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortHwLinkError
item.description: A crossbar port is expected to have its HW_LINK_OK bit set but it is not Data field bits contain the crossbar ID bits contain the port number for which the error occurred and bits contain the port status Minor

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortFeError
item.description: A connected crossbar port was found to have its FE bit set Data field bits contain the crossbar ID bits contain the port number for which the error occurred and bits contain the port status Minor

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXinLinkInitError
item.description: There was an error while initializing the Cell ControllerXbc interface The data field contains the address of the Cell Controller CSR for which the error occurred

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXinLinkInitFailed
item.description: The CC XBC link failed to initialize

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiGetMfgModeNotInit
item.description: EFI is unable to determine current system mode The EFISAL interface is not initialized This interface should have been initialized before now This event indicates an internal EFI error EFI will continue executing

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiBmcMfgModeInvalid
item.description: The BMC has returned an invalid system mode Data Field the invalid mode Expected values are or

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiEnterMfgModeNotInit
item.description: EFI is unable to specify a new system mode The EFISAL interface point is not initialized This interface should have been initialized before now This event indicates an internal EFI error EFI will continue executing in the current mode

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiExitMfgModeNotInit
item.description: EFI is unable to enter normal system mode The EFISAL interface is not initialized This interface should have been initialized before now This event indicates an internal EFI error EFI will continue executing in the current mode

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiTaccessServiceNotInit
item.description: EFI is unable to initialize part of the SALEFI interface This crucial service provides access to certain BMC functionality such as the security system EFI will halt Data Field Return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtTreeNodeNotFound
item.description: A needed tree node was not found The data field contains the ASCII name of the tree node that was not found

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSystemStateRunningErr
item.description: EFI is unable to modify the system state from 'booting' to 'running' This is done as part of Exit Boot Services The system will not be able to enter a sleep mode Data Field For errors this data is zero For warnings this data indicates the current system state as Error booting running attention fault booting attention

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPalBusConfigIncompatible
item.description: CPUBusConfigValue setting in options as been compared with what is reported by PAL as settable and CPUBusConfigValue is specifying at least one bit that is not supported by this version of PAL using the Get Processor Bus Dependent Configuration Features This chassis code is emitted in pairs the first data field contains the PAL expected values the second data field contains the requested setting from options

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPalGetBusFeaturesFailed
item.description: Firmware was unable to correctly issue the Get Processor Bus Dependent Configuration Features command

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemDimmPairMismatch
item.description: A pair of DIMMs installed in the system are mismatched and that pair of DIMMs will not be used The data field indicates which pair of DIMMs are mismatched in the format xXBXA where X is the number of the rank that is mismatched

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiPosseLibNotInit
item.description: EFI is unable to initialize internal library This collection of internal services is required for much of EFI's functionality EFI is halting

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSecurityNotInit
item.description: EFI is unable to initialize the security level The privilege level of the system may or may not be Admin It is likely certain EFI facilities will be unavailable EFI will continue booting but security may be compromised Data Field Return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSecInvalidSysmode
item.description: EFI detected an invalid value for its internal privilege level This value is stored within SAL EFI will continue but system security may be compromised Data Field The invalid privilege level

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSecSetPassLevelErr
item.description: EFI detected an invalid privilege level when setting a BMC password Only the levels of Admin (x) and User (x) are permitted Data Field the invalid privilege level

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMdtBad
item.description: SFW has determined that the Memory Data Table (MDT) table is invalid

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCpuBadCoreFixedRatio
item.description: Processor has incompatible fixed core ratio Data Local CPU Number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootAllCpusSlatedForCompatDeconfig
item.description: Data A bitmask for which CPUs are slated to be deconfigured

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcReadRemoteRouteError
item.description: An error occurred while reading a crossbar remote route table or an unexpectedinvalid value was read from the table The data field consists of the crossbar ID () the port number of which the table was read () and the return status of the read call ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcReadNeighborInfoError
item.description: An error occurred while trying to read the PORT[n]_NEIGHBOR_INFO crossbar CSR The data field consists of the crossbar ID () and port number () for which the CSR was read

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemDimmQuadMismatch
item.description: A quad of DIMMs installed in the system are mismatched and that quad of DIMMs will not be used The data field indicates which quad of DIMMs are mismatched in the format xXDXCXBXA where X is the number of the rank that is mismatched

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemDimmFailed
item.description: The DIMM at the physical location given by the data field had excessive errors and has been marked as 'FAILED' by firmware

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortOeError
item.description: A XBC port was expected to be functional but its OE bit was not set The data field consists of the contents of the port_status CSR () the XBC number () and the port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortStatusError
item.description: Unable to read the PORT_STATUS CSR for a XBC port The data field consists of the contents of the PORT_STATUS CSR () the XBC number () and the port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortLandmined
item.description: A XBC port was unexpectedly found to be landmined The data field consists of the XBC number () and the port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdIncompatibleCpuSpeeds
item.description: Reporting cell tried to rendezvous with a cell with processors that are running at a different speed The data field lists the offending cell

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCellLinkNotInit
item.description: The link between the local CC and the local XBC is unexpectedly not initialized The data field is the XIN_LINK_STATE CC CSR value

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricInvalidXbcNum
item.description: A value that was expected to be a XBC number was found to be an invalid XBC number The data field is the invalid XBC number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricInvalidXbcPortNum
item.description: A value that was expected to be a valid XBC port number was found to be invalid The data field is the XBC number () and the invalid XBC port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtUtilitiesLedParamError
item.description: A bad parameter was passed to the utilities function that manipulates the LED on replaceable parts The offending parameter is displayed in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricUnexpectedNtype
item.description: A neighbor type read from a XBC PORT_NEIGHBOR_INFO CSR was different than the expected neighbor type This event is emitted twice first with expected data and second with actual data Data field XBC number () XBC port number () expected type () Data field XBC number () XBC port number () actual neighbor type ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricPortNotCc
item.description: A XBC port number was unexpectedly found to not be a valid XBCCC port The data field consists of the XBC number () and the port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricPortNotXbc
item.description: A XBC port was unexpectedly found to be an invalid XBCXBC port The data field consists of the XBC number () and the port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricUnexpectedNChip
item.description: The XBC neighbor chip number does not match the expected value for this topology The data field contains the expected neighbor chip number () and the actual neighbor chip number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricUnexpectedNPort
item.description: The XBC neighbor port number does not match the expected value for this topology The data field contains the expected neighbor port number () and the actual neighbor port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootNvmWriteToBmcTokenFailure
item.description: A write to a BMC token has failed This is a boot warning condition Data Upper bits BMC failure return code Lower bits BMC token number that failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtUtilitiesLedError
item.description: The utilities system reported an error while trying to carry out the command to turn on flash or turn off the LED The status returned by the command is displayed in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtDuplicateCpuIds
item.description: cpus think that they have the same ID within the cell Typically this would mean that PAL reported the same cpu id for more than cpu on a bus The cpuid is in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHp-uxCrashdumpStarted
item.description: OS crashdump started (D)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHp-uxHexFaultCode
item.description: OS legacy PA hex fault code (Bxxx) Possible IO error or system panic

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHp-uxDumpStatus
item.description: A memory dump occurred on the system or on one partition in a cellular system The dump occurred due to either a nonrecoverable error or by user request EFxx is the OS dump status (the successfailure of the writing of the dump) EF success (followed by either EFA successful dump with sync or EF successful dump without sync) EFFF a general error EFFE dump path assertion failure EFFD no dump was taken by default choice or failure EFFC dump was aborted by user

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSettingProcTimeoutFail
item.description: SFW has failed to set the processor timeout value via a PAL call Data PAL call return value

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSecInitVerifyErr
item.description: During EFI security initialization the attempt to determine what privilege level a blank password provides failed Most likely this indicates the BMC has failed EFI assumes that the BMC has failed and will attempt to continue booting Some EFI functionality may be unavailable Data Field Return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSecInitCloseErr
item.description: As part of normal security initialization EFI attempted to issue a close session to the BMC (Ie force the BMC to GUEST mode) This attempt failed EFI is unable to initialize the security system EFI will continue but security may be compromised Data Field Return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSecInitOpenErr
item.description: As part of normal security initialization EFI attempted to issue an open session to the BMC in order to raise the privilege level to the highest permitted by a blank password This attempt failed EFI is unable to initialize the security system Data Field Return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSecInitWriteErr
item.description: As part of normal security initialization EFI attempted to record the current privilege level This attempt failed EFI is unable to initialize the security system Data Field Return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiSecInitWriteDenied
item.description: As part of normal security initialization EFI attempted to record the current privilege level This attempt failed with a privilege violation error EFI is unable to initialize the security system Data Field Return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHp-uxDumpWriteError
item.description: OS dump error writing image area to disk (E)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtErrDeadlockResetDetected
item.description: Early in bootstrap the coherency controller (CC) registers are checked for Deadlock Recovery Reset This chassis code indicates that CC logs will be stored to NVRAM

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemParityErr
item.description: SFW detected a memory address parity error The data field contains the physical location of DIMM that saw the parity error

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemDimmLoadOrdErr
item.description: The loading order of the DIMMs is incorrect The cell is halted

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemRefreshStartError
item.description: Timeout Waiting for SDRAM parts to become ready mem_status[] Refresh Control Register

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemExtBaseboardIncompatible
item.description: The version of Memory extender installed in the system has not been qualified to work with the version of the baseboard installed in the system

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricDifferentTopologies
item.description: There is a fabric topology mismatch with the XBCs in the complex Data Field (Topology of XBC ) | Topology of destination XBC x Topology not yet determined x Domelight x UTurn (Left cabinet) x UTurn (Right cabinet) x CrossFlex x UTurn

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricInvalidXbc2XbcPort
item.description: While routing the XBC to XBC ports an invalid port was encountered The data field is the crossbar number () and the port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricGetNeighborInfoError
item.description: The XBC could not get neighbor Minor Data Field XBC # | internal port attempting to access neighbor

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcRoutingErrorState
item.description: For the XBC being routed routing has already been attempted but an error occurred Inspect chassis codes from other cells for more details regarding the nature of the problem The data field consists of the XBC number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtNoNvmErrLogSpace
item.description: This means that the error event log cannot be logged to the persistent storage The data field gives the event type that was supposed to be logged

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortError
item.description: An XBC port was found to have an unexpected error The data field consists of the crossbar number () and the current port errors ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortRouteAround
item.description: During fabric routing a port on a XBC was found in error or had been previously marked as in error PDC will route around this XBC port Data Field XBC number () and external XBC port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcUnexpectedState
item.description: Data field the unexpected forward progress state () XBC number () Cell number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcRoutingStateTimeout
item.description: A crossbar was found to be in an unexpected forward progress state during fabric routing This crossbar stayed in the unexpected state until Fabric Discovery timed out Data field unexpected forward progress () XBC number () Cell number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcNeighborPortNotRoutable
item.description: An XBC port was found that is not healthy This indicates at least one of the following about the port Hardware link is not okay Presence detect is false Fatal error detected SBE detected LPE detected Port landmined The data field of the chassis code indicates which port is unhealthy as well as the fabric routing state before the problem was encountered

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCcToXbcError
item.description: The CC to XBC link is not viable

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricRouteXbcError
item.description: There was a problem performing remote routing on the local XBC Chassis codes sent before this one may provide more details about the exact nature of the problem The data field consists of the XBC number that failed routing ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricMaxBrokenLinks
item.description: Two or more XBCXBC links were found to be broken The data field is the XBC number () and a bit map of the ports broken ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcSemaphoreTakeoverFailed
item.description: After unlocking the XBC Global Semaphore for a takeover this cell did not get the semaphore

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcForceUnlockSm4Timeout
item.description: When a cell holds an XBC semaphore for an extended period of time fabric will attempt to takeover the semaphore so that the rest of the cells will have access to it Fabric will attempt to take the SM for a period of time If it is unable to unlock the SM within the timeout period it will send this chassis code and halt the cell Data field XBC number () and current owner (cell) of the semaphore ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcGetGlobalSm4Timeout
item.description: During Fabric Discovery the cell will wait until it gets the XBC's Global Semaphore It waits for a very long time This chassis code indicates that the wait has timed out

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcReleaseSm4Timeout
item.description: The XBC Release Semaphore timeout is designed to fail last The semaphore could not be released Any other cell (even outside the PD) may be blocked because the XBC is a global resource Data field current semaphore owner () XBC number () port number () cell number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMpBatteryFailure
item.description: Management Processor Firmware detected improper data in NVRAM (bad checksums) Either the NVRAM layout changed or the Management Processor Battery may not be maintaining the data through AC power cycles

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMpSoftwareError
item.description: Management Processor Firmware detected a software error and is logging an event The data represents data associated with the error seen

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMpI2cCommError
item.description: An IC Communication failure with the Baseboard Management Controller was detected Without IC communication the system cannot be powered onoff or reset

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtRomCrcError
item.description: A stored CRC value did not match the calculated CRC value for the specified address

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIoIdentifyIoBpFailed
item.description: See Summary

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuRevisionMismatch
item.description: cpus in the system are reporting different revisions This event will be emitted in groups of with the two revisions reported in the first data fields and the cpu number in the rd data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuFreqMismatch
item.description: This chassis code will be emitted in pairs cpus are reporting that they are running at different frequencies The two frequencies are reported in the data fields

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuOverclocked
item.description: The rating for the cpu and the actual speed will be emitted in sequential event data fields

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCmplxProfilIncoherent
item.description: The complex profile is stored in NVRAM on the MP and each cell All copies must match For this error to be generated not only is the MP's copy of the complex profile invalid but not all of the cell's copies match

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtDuplicateCabinet
item.description: The MP detected or more cabinets with the same cabinet number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIdCommandRequired
item.description: The complex identification Minor in group A of the complex profile is invalid The MP (Manageability Processor) command 'ID' must be run The SSKEY hardware is required

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtNvramBatteryFail
item.description: The battery on the SBCH is below the safe threshold The battery can be replaced online

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPartitionTimeoutReset
item.description: The partition is being reset because its watchdog timer expired and automatic restart is enabled

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcWatchdogTimedOut
item.description: The processor dependent hardware controller (PDHC) on the cell board had its watchdog timer expire The PDHC will reset the watchdog as the main program runs If the watchdog does not get reset within seconds the timer will expire resetting the PDHC

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtAbortPowerupOth
item.description: The Cabinet Power Up request was aborted due to ambient air over temperature

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtAbortPwrupBps
item.description: The power requirements for the cabinet exceeds the capabilities of the available Bulk Power Supplies The PM section of the Utilities Subsystems keeps a tally of the power requirements for all installed entities in a cabinet The power available from the Bulk Power Supplies does not meet the requirements of the installed entities according to the Cabinet Power Tally

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtAbortStartBlowr
item.description: When given a power up request the cabinet had to abort the start up due to less than the required number of Cabinet Blowers installed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtAbortStartIofan
item.description: When given a power up request the cabinet had to abort the start up due to less than the required number of IO fans present

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtAcDeleted
item.description: The AC power connected to the PDCA (Power Distribution Control Assembly) was removed The data field contains the physical location of the PDCA The PDCA source that was deleted can be identified by the implementation dependent field (data byte ) of the physical location data byte[] for PDCA for PDCA

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBlowrFail
item.description: A cabinet main blower has failed Depending on the number of blowers still operating the cabinet may or may not shut down View the Error Log entries to determine if the cabinet is operating If many log entries call out entities powering off during the same time frame as this BLOWR_FAIL the cabinet has probably shutdown Carefully review the log for the first few events within the same time frame for the root cause of the problem The GSP command PS will show a detailed power status for a cabinet If the V LED on the Front Panel Board is not lit power is not enabled to the cabinet This is an indication the cabinet blowers have probably gone from N to N status requiring an immediate cabinet shutdown

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBpsFail48flt
item.description: A Volt DC Converter powered by the specified PDCA failed on the designated Bulk Power Supply The PDCA powering the converter on the BPS that failed can be identified by the implementation dependent field (data byte ) of the BPS' physical location data byte[] for PDCA for PDCA

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBpsFailFanflt
item.description: The designated Bulk Power Supply is reporting its fan has failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBpsFailOt
item.description: The Volt DC Converter powered by the specified PDCA in the designated Bulk Power Supply is in over temp condition The PDCA powering the converter on the BPS that failed can be identified by the activity status (last byte of chassis code) e PDCA f PDCA

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBpsNotRedundant
item.description: The number of functioning Bulk Power Supplies has decreased to where the Cabinet Power supplied (number of available Bulk Power Supplies times power output per each) minus the estimated Cabinet Power consumed is greater than but less than the output of one Bulk Power Supply

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBpsOvervoltage
item.description: The PM has detected the value of V power as measured on the UGUY board has exceeded an upper threshold

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBpsUndervoltage
item.description: The PM has detected the value of V power as measured on the UGUY board has fallen below a lower threshold

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCabFanFail
item.description: A cabinet fan has failed Depending on the number of cabinet fans still operating the cabinet may or may not shut down View the Error Log entries to determine if the cabinet is operating

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHkpOvervoltage
item.description: Housekeeping power has exceeded expected levels

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHkpUndervoltage
item.description: Housekeeping power has fallen below expected levels

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIllegalBpsCfgOrPhaseFlt
item.description: Through failures or reconfiguration the BPS for the cabinet named are illegally configured There must be a BPS connected to each phase of the power Phase feeds BPS slots & phase feeds slots & and phase feeds & There must be a BPS connected to each phase If BPS are installed in a cabinet in slots and & were empty this would be an illegal configuration They should be installed in and or and or some combination thereof The PDCA physical location determines which phase is configured incorrectly Data Byte (implementation dependent field) indicates the PDCA number used when the configuration error occurred

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIllegalBpsid
item.description: A Bulk Power Supply is reporting an unknown BPS ID The Bulk Power Supply will not be powered up and added to the Power Available tally If cabinet is not powered up it will refuse to power up until this fault is corrected

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtInletOvertempHi
item.description: The cabinet's Ambient Air Sensor detected a change in air temperature entering the overtemphigh range The Cabinet will be shutting itself down to prevent component damage

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtInletOvertempLo
item.description: The cabinet's Ambient Air Sensor detected a change in air temperature crossing to the low range The air temperature may be rising or falling This is just a reporting of entering the overtemplow range

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtInletOvertempMid
item.description: The cabinet's Ambient Air Sensor detected a change in air temperature crossing to the mid range The air temperature may be rising or falling This is just a reporting of entering the overtempmid range

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIofanFail
item.description: An IO Chassis cooling fan has failed Depending on the number of fans still operating the cabinet may or may not shut down View Error Log entries to determine if the cabinet is operating If many log entries call out entities powering off during the same time frame as this IOFAN_FAIL the cabinet has probably shutdown Carefully review the log for the first few events within the same time frame for the root cause of the problem The Guardian Service Processor command PS will show a detailed power status for a cabinet The V LED on the Front Panel Board not lit power is not enabled to the cabinet indicating the cabinet IO Chassis fans have probably gone from N to N status requiring an immediate cabinet shutdown

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPowerOverload
item.description: This code is issued when the Cabinet Power supplied (number of Bulk Power Supplies times power output per each) minus the estimated Cabinet Power consumed drops below Utilities firmware will not allow a cabinet in this state to power up (see ABORT_PWRUP_BPS) Utilities firmware will not shut down a cabinet in this state However there is a possibility of a cabinet brownout making the cabinet unreliable

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtShutdownBlowr
item.description: After a BLOWR_FAIL there were N blowers functioning This is an illegal condition causing immediate cabinet shutdown to prevent component damage

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtShutdownIofan
item.description: After a IOFAN_FAIL there were N fans functioning This is an illegal condition causing immediate cabinet shutdown to prevent component damage

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXucFanFail
item.description: One of two fans in the Utility chassis of the IO Expansion Cabinet has failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCluWatchdogReset
item.description: The Watchdog Timer checks for inactivity or hung state of the Cabinet Level Utilities (CLU) portion of the UGUY During activity the timer is continually reset If the timer expires it will automatically reset the CLU microprocessor This will not affect running partitions

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEepromInvalidCksm
item.description: An invalid checksum was received when reading the FRUID EEPROM for the device named in the chassis code If this is a single error the fault lies with the named FRU If there are many INVALID_CKSM entries in the Event Log there is probably a problem with the IC bus

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHbpbBoardPowerFault
item.description: One or more of the System Backplane Power Boards is reporting a DC Fault through the System Backplane Local Power Monitor The physical location of the failing power board is in the Data Field of the event

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHiobEepromRdFail
item.description: An attempt to read the EEPROM (FRUID) on the IO Backplane Board failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHiopbEepromRdFail
item.description: An attempt to read the EEPROM (FRUID) on the IO Backplane Power Board failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHiopbLpmFltRdFail
item.description: An attempt to read the Local Power Monitor Fault register on the IO Backplane Power Board failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHiopbOvertemp
item.description: The Local Power Monitor of the named IO Chassis is reporting a Power Brick over temperature condition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHiopbPowerFault
item.description: The Local Power Monitor on the named IO Chassis has reported a power fault condition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtHiopbVoltMrgnFail
item.description: The Local Power Monitor on the named IO Power Board failed to properly margin the power as commanded

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSbchEepromRdFail
item.description: Either by command or as part of initialization the data from a FRUID EEPROM failed a read command This does not necessarily mean the FRU has failed just that the FRUID data cannot be read

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtUguyEepromRdFail
item.description: Either by command or as part of initialization the data from a FRUID EEPROM failed a read command This does not necessarily mean the FRU has failed just that the FRUID can't be read

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSysBkpEepromRdFail
item.description: An attempt to read the EEPROM (FRUID) on the System Backplane failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSysBkpI2cRdFail
item.description: A read command on the system backplane IC bus failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSysBkpI2cWrFail
item.description: A write command on the system backplane IC bus failed The type of command that failed can be identified by the activity status field (last byte) of the encoded field B RC Cable Configuration Register write C Backplane Voltage Margin Register write Flex circuit configuration register write

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSysBkpPowerFault
item.description: The Local Power Monitor on the named System Backplane has detected a power fault The failing Backplane Power Board status is read from the Backplane LPM IC interface register and the value is placed in the data field of the event (bits )

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSysBkpVoltMrgnFail
item.description: Margining voltage to the System Backplane has failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtWriteFruDataFail
item.description: An attempt to write data to the FRUID EEPROM by the MFG level MP command WF failed The FRU handle of the failing FRUID is embedded in the two uppermost bytes of the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuFanFail
item.description: The fan on a CPU is not operating in a manner that provides enough air flow to cool the processor

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuFanSlow
item.description: The fan on a CPU is operating in a manner that provides enough air flow to cool the processor but is not at normal operation

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtDnaFanFail
item.description: The fan on a CC chip is not operating in a manner that provides enough air flow to cool the processor

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtDnaFanSlow
item.description: The fan on a CC chip is operating in a manner that provides enough air flow to cool the processor but is not at normal operation

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcToSysfwRevMismtch
item.description: System FW and the PDHC have incompatible shared memory interface revisions Data byte is the PDHC's supported ICM revision number Data byte is System FW's supported ICM revision number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhCtrlrFwMismatch
item.description: The MP checked the FW revision of the PDHC identified in the physical location data field and discovered that it did not recognize the revision as one that it has been qualed with This is an unsupported configuration

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCellPowerFault
item.description: The local Power Monitor is reporting a fault with the named Cell Power Board The data field of this event can be decoded as follows where a bit set in any of the status fields indicates a fault data byte (power_good ) | (power_fault) data byte Cell Power Board converters status bits[] memory power bricks status bits[] power if bus bricks status bits[] JAB core power bricks status data byte Cell converters status bit clock power status bit cache power status bit link power status bit CC core power status bit FSB power status bit V status data byte CPU module converters status bit CPU module core power status bit CPU module core power status bit CPU module core power status bit CPU module core power status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuInitNodeError
item.description: The CPU node retuned an error when calling its initialize node function The specific status is displayed in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuExecuteCmdError
item.description: ExecuteCommand issues commands that execute on remote CPUs via IPI interrupts If the command failed to execute this event is printed and the data field contains the status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuCmdStateInvalid
item.description: A remote CPU is in a state where it cannot receive and execute a new command The current status of the CPU is provided in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuPalProcError
item.description: An error was encountered when executing a PAL_PROC This code will be emitted in pairs The Proc INDEX will be in the data of the first chassis code The status is in the second data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCpuLoadingError
item.description: CPUs not loaded in correct order Correct loading order is CPU

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPersistantError
item.description: The XBC logged a SBE or LPE after they should have been cleared Either the clear failed or a new error was logged immediately Data field XBC number () port number () port status Minor ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcLinkTestError
item.description: The CC to XBC Link pattern test failed Data Field This event will be emitted three times st event XBC number () port number () nd event expected pattern () rd event actual data read ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPltfrmStorageReadErr
item.description: System firmware was unable to complete a platform storage read command from the utilities system The exact status printed in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPltfrmStorageWriteErr
item.description: System firmware was unable to complete a platform storage write command The actual status is returned in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtTreeNodeErrorSequencer
item.description: The Sequencer was unable to find the tree node it needed to complete an operation The tree node is in the ASCII in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPartitionVariableError
item.description: System firmware attempted to read a partition variable from the GSP and store it in options An error was encountered during this process The data field contains the partition variable element ID that was being processed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCellRedundtPowerFault
item.description: One or more power converters on the Cell or Cell Power Board has reported a fault However because of redundancy in the power system the power to the Cell is still good The data field contains detailed power fault location Minor that is specific to each platform

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPalProcConfigIncompatible
item.description: CPUProcConfigValue setting in options as been compared with what is reported by PAL as settable and CPUProcConfigValue is specifying at least one bit that is not supported by this version of PAL using the Get Processor Dependent Features This chassis code is emitted in pairs the first data field contains the PAL expected values the second data field contains the requested setting from options

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPalGetProcFeaturesFailed
item.description: System firmware was unable to successfully issue the PAL_GET_PROC_FEATURES PAL proc The data field is unused

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcCriticalDebug
item.description: This event is a tool to aid in the debugging and testing of firmware

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCluUndefinedCase
item.description: The CLU has encountered an undefined case in its control flow

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCellVoltageMarginUnkn
item.description: The Cell voltage margin settings do not match the Normal % or % values

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcAssertionFailed
item.description: For debug purposes many assumptions made by the PDHC developer(s) are checked at runtime If this event log is seen it indicates that the hardware or software is in an unknown state For developer debug purposes the data field describes where in the code that the error was detected Data Bytes[] The line number within the source code file where the error was detected Data Bytes[] The first characters of the source code file name

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcFirmwareUnknownErr
item.description: An unknown error has been detected by the PDHC firmware For developer debug purposes the data field describes where in the code that the error was detected Data Bytes[] The line number within the source code file where the error was detected Data Bytes[] The first characters of the source code file name

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcI2cWriteFailed
item.description: An attempt to write to a device on the PDHC's IC bus has failed The devices on the IC bus are the Cell's FRU EEPROM the Cell Power Board's FRU EEPROM the voltage margining DtoA converters and if they are accessible the CPU Module Power Pods' FRU EEPROMs The Data field Minor contains Minor that can identify the exact device that has failed Refer to the Cell ERS for a mapping of IC device addresses to devices Data Bytes[] Reserved Data Bytes[] IC Device Address Data Bytes[] Starting Word Address Data Bytes[] Size of attempted access (in bytes)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcI2cReadFailed
item.description: An attempt to read from a device on the PDHC's IC bus has failed The devices on the IC bus are the Cell's FRU EEPROM the Cell Power Board's FRU EEPROM the voltage margining DtoA converters and if they are accessible the CPU Module Power Pods' FRU EEPROMs The Data field Minor contains Minor that can identify the exact device that has failed Refer to the Cell ERS for a mapping of IC device addresses to devices Data Bytes[] Reserved Data Bytes[] IC Device Address Data Bytes[] Starting Word Address Data Bytes[] Size of attempted access (in bytes)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcSmbusWriteFailed
item.description: An attempt to write to a device on the PDHC's SM bus has failed The devices on the SM bus are the CPU modules' FRU EEPROMs the CPU modules' Processor Minor ROMs and the CPU modules' thermal sensors The Data field Minor contains Minor that can identify the exact device that has failed Refer to the Cell ERS for a mapping of SM Bus device addresses to devices Data Bytes[] Reserved Data Bytes[] SM bus Device Address Data Bytes[] Starting Word Address Data Bytes[] Size of attempted access (in bytes)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcSmbusReadFailed
item.description: An attempt to read from a device on the PDHC's SM bus has failed The devices on the SM bus are the CPU modules' FRU EEPROMs the CPU modules' Processor Minor ROMs and the CPU modules' thermal sensors The Data field Minor contains Minor that can identify the exact device that has failed Refer to the Cell ERS for a mapping of SM Bus device addresses to devices Data Bytes[] Reserved Data Bytes[] SM bus Device Address Data Bytes[] Starting Word Address Data Bytes[] Size of attempted access (in bytes)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFrequencyProgramFailed
item.description: The PDHC did not read valid frequency Minor from the CPU modules' or Cell's FRU EEPROMs or the frequency registers would not update properly Following this event the Cell will not boot until the problem is corrected and Cell Power has been turned off then on again using the PE command

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSysFwFlashUpdateError
item.description: An error has occurred while updating System FW More details about the update failure may be available as displayed by the Firmware Update Utility (FWUU)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcUnexpectedReset
item.description: The PDHC firmware was reset for some unknown reason

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuTmpSensorSetupFail
item.description: A hardware fault prevented the PDHC from configuring the thermal sensor(s) on one or more of the CPU modules Following detection of this fault condition the Cell will be prevented from booting until the Cell is powered 'off' then 'on' using the PE command

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuModuleThermalert
item.description: A CPU module's temperature has exceed the high temperature threshold As a result of this event an irrevocable minute timer will begin At the end of minutes the offending CPU module will be powered off by the Cell hardware The Cell must be powered off then on using the MP's PE command before the CPU module will be powered again

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcFlashUpdateError
item.description: An error occurred while updating the PDHC firmware More specific details of the update error may be displayed by the Firmware Update utility running on the MP

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCellTypMismatchWSysfw
item.description: The cell type (IPF or PA) does not match System FW type The cell type is detected based on Minor stored in CPU modules' FRUID EEPROMs The System FW type is determined based on data that is embedded in the System FW ROM image This is checked each time Cell power transitions from off to on and each time the System FW is updated Following the detection of this mismatch the Cell will not be allowed to boot until the problem has been resolved

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcPdhArbiterTimeout
item.description: This event is emitted after the PDHC has waited longer than a maximum expected time for the PDH arbiter to grant it control of the PDH bus The PDHC will continue waiting for control of the PDH bus until the arbiter grants it control or the Cell is powered off using the MP's PE command While waiting for the PDH bus the PDHC will NOT perform its normal duties such as monitoring the Cell status and passing messages from the system to the MP and the PDHC heartbeat will not blink

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhcGetSm4Timeout
item.description: This event is emitted after the PDHC has waited longer than a maximum expected time to obtain control of the PDH bus semaphore The PDHC will continue waiting for control of the PDH bus semaphore until System FW relinquishes control of the semaphore or the Cell is powered off using the MP's PE command While waiting for the PDH bus semaphore the PDHC will NOT perform its normal duties such as monitoring the Cell status and passing messages from the system to the MP and the PDHC heartbeat will not blink The data field contains debug data that may be useful for developers Data_byte[] last value read from PDHC's address for the microSemaphore register Data_byte[] boolean indicator (setnot_set) of whether the PDHC's flag is set Data_byte[] boolean indicator (setnot_set) of whether the System FW's flag is set

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIpmiBmc2hostMsgFailure
item.description: This event indicates that an error occurred while transmitting an IPMI message in the BMCHOST direction The data field contains more detailed Minor about the source of the error Data Bytes & form a bit IPMI error indicator that has the following values and meanings IPMI_HOST_BUSY_TIMEOUT The PDHC could not put a message in the BMCHOST hardware message queue for over seconds so the pending message(s) were dropped IPMI_INVALID_MSG_SIZE The MP sent an IPMI message response that has an embedded size indicator that is less than bytes or greater than the size of the message data The poorly formed message response will be dropped IPMI_BMCHOST_Q_FULL The BMCHOST message queue in the PDHC is full so a message response from the MP has been dropped

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtEfiDebugLevelTokenErr
item.description: EFI was unable to read the initial debug level from the BMC token EFI will continue with an unknown value for the debug level Data Field Return status from internal EFI function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXbcPortNotLandmined
item.description: A XBC port was unexpectedly found to not be landmined The data field consists of the XBC number () and the port number ()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricValidateError
item.description: The number of landmined XBC ports was not within the allowable range There is a minimum number of landmined ports because some ports are always unused There is a maximum number of landmined ports because there is a limit to the number of broken links allowed in a system The data field shows the number of landmined ports found

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricISRInvalidBkp
item.description: Data field contains the backplane type found During Intra SKD Routing the backplane type detected was either a Medel backplane or was unrecognized The backplane could therefore not be routed This is a firmware sanity check Data Field system type

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinWrZeroErrMaskError
item.description: Prior to initializing the CC to XBC link the XIN error mask should be zeroed out to prevent spurious errors from interfering with the link initialization This write to zero out the error mask failed Data Field (cell ) | return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCcPriModeRegRdStatus
item.description: The Coherency Controller's (CC) XIN link did not initialize properly The data field contains the return status from an attempted read of the CC Primary Error Mode CSR ( SUCCESS)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCcPriModeRegRdData
item.description: The Coherency Controller's (CC) XIN link did not initialize properly The data field contains the data read from the CC Primary Error Mode CSR

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCcErrMaskRegRdStatus
item.description: The Coherency Controller's (CC) XIN link did not initialize properly The data field contains the return status from an attempted read of the CC Primary Error Mode CSR ( SUCCESS)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCcErrMaskRegRdData
item.description: The Coherency Controller's (CC) XIN link did not initialize properly The data field contains the data read from the CC Error Mask CSR

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXingNeighborPortBad
item.description: The neighbor's port connected to the link being crossed is not routable This was the first attempt to cross the link PDC will now look for another link it can cross DATA (xbcNum ) | (port )

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricISRRdFwdProgErr
item.description: Fabric read error Data field (XBC number | return status)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricGetNeighborMaxLinksBroken
item.description: Too many crossbar links are broken Cell cannot boot halting Data field XBC number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPmAssertionFailed
item.description: For debug purposes many assumptions made by the PM developer(s) are checked at runtime If this event log is seen it will either indicate that the hardware is in a unknown state that is not handled by the PM or that a programming bug has been found For developer debug purposes the data field describes where in the code that the error was detected Data Bytes[] The line number within the source code file where the error was detected Data Bytes[] The first characters of the source code file name

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPmFirmwareUnknownErr
item.description: An unknown error has been detected by the PM firmware For developer debug purposes the data field describes where in the code that the error was detected Data Bytes[] The line number within the source code file where the error was detected Data Bytes[] The first characters of the source code file name

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPmCriticalDebug
item.description: This event is a tool to aid in the debugging and testing of firmware

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricLinkCorErrTestFailure
item.description: Failed link testing to ensure that SBE and LPE errors are detected properly by the XBC The XBC did not detect any errors Data field indicates the return status ( err detected no err detected XBC accesses failed)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtInvalidCabinetNumber
item.description: The data field contains the cabinet number that is invalid

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdIncompatibleFwRevs
item.description: The cell indicated in the data field is at a different firmware revision than the reporting cell This is determined by evaluating the checksums of the rom images

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPmI2cWriteFailed
item.description: An attempt to write to a device on the PM's IC bus has failed The Data field contains Minor that can identify the exact device that has failed Refer to the UGUY ERS for a mapping of IC device addresses to devices Data Bytes[] Reserved Data Bytes[] IC Device Address Data Bytes[] Starting Word Address Data Bytes[] Size of attempted access (in bytes)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPmI2cReadFailed
item.description: An attempt to read from a device on the PM's IC bus has failed This event is only emitted when the PM is reading a BPS's The Data field contains Minor that can identify the exact device that has failed Refer to the UGUY ERS for a mapping of IC device addresses to devices Data Bytes[] Reserved Data Bytes[] IC Device Address (to convert to BPS slot number subtract and divide by ) Data Bytes[] Starting Word Address Data Bytes[] Size of attempted access (in bytes)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCellInfoError
item.description: An error was encountered trying to obtain the data required for the cell Minor structure in ICM The data field is an ASCII message that indicates the Minor that was not found

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSlaveConsoleSetupError
item.description: An error was encountered establishing the slave cells use of the diva console

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtRegistryMoveToCoreCellError
item.description: An error was encountered trying to relocate the registry on a slave cell to point to the core cells main memory structures

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtProfileGroupCCrcError
item.description: The Calculated CRC for the group C Partition Profile did not match the stored value The expected value and the actual value will be emitted in sequential chassis codes

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMcCoreCellSelectFail
item.description: Not able to find a core cell in the PD during a global MCA error processing

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricAssertFabricUtils
item.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric The firmware is not able to analyze this error Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command HPUX also saves these logs in the varstmlogsos directory and they can be viewed using the slview utility

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSalPmiFwError
item.description: An internal firmware error was encountered This is usually caused by a bad parameter passed to a function corrupt memory corrupt malloc tables or something similar The data field contains the IP address of the function that encountered the error

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtOlaWrongNumberCells
item.description: During the on line addition of a cell the partition adding the cell has determined inconsistent data as to which cell is being added The cell addition will be aborted and the partition will resume execution without the new cell

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXbcRouteSourceCellPortErr
item.description: An error occurred while reading the routing from the source cell's port on the source XBC Data Field (source cell | source XBC )

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaCellIncompatible
item.description: OLA cell cannot be added because it has resources that are not compatible with those already in the partition Data field specifies the physical location of the cell which is incompatible and on which the OLA was attempted The preceding chassis code or codes should already have been emitted specifying what the actual incompatibility was The OLA cell will NOT be added to the partition and the existing partition should not be affected

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaCellDidNotReachRendezvous
item.description: Root Cell attempted to OLA a cell which hung somewhere in the OLA process the cell released from BIB but never made it to its final rendezvous state Data field contains physical location of the hung OLA cell The OLA cell will NOT be added to the partition and the existing partition should not be affected

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaCellStillAtBib
item.description: Root cell attempted to OLA a cell that was never released from BIB Data field contains the physical location of the cell that is being OLAD

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaCellUnexpectedCellState
item.description: Partition attempted to OLA a cell in an unexpected Cell state Data Field contains the unexpected cell state of the OLA cell The OLA cell will NOT be added to the partition and the existing partition should not be affected

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaCellCantReachAliveCells
item.description: Root cell will emit this chassis code indicating the OLA cell could reach all cells in the alive set of the existing partition Data field will contain the physical location of the OLA cell This chassis code should immediately follow a chassis code indicating exactly which cell the OLA cell could not reach The OLA cell will not be added to the partition and the partition will be unaffected

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMixedCpuCoreFreqInstalled
item.description: CPU's of mixed maximum core frequencies are installed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtXinInitIntermittentFailure
item.description: The Cell ControllerXBC link initialization is having an intermittent failure The data field contains the number of initialization sequences that failed before being successful

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhErrClearOlaSteeringBit
item.description: PDC failed clearing the OLA steering bit in the PDH FPGA microstatus register Data field contains the physical location of the cell with the failure This can only happen on an OLA cell and will cause that cell to reset and not to join the existing partition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdatePdAddrMap
item.description: The attempt to update the PD Addr Map to include OLA cell failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdatePdPdt
item.description: Attempt to update the partition PDT with OLA cell PDT data has failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdateCellMap
item.description: Attempt to update the cell map to include the OLA Cell failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCc2XbcLinkInitFailed
item.description: Fabric Discovery's final attempt to initialize the local cell's CC to Crossbar Chip (XBC) link has failed This cell cannot talk to the fabric Data link init state bit read from the CC Link State register

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFwVirtualMappingError
item.description: An internal firmware error was encountered This is usually caused by a bad parameter passed to a function corrupt memory corrupt malloc tables or something similar The data field contains the physical address that failed mapping to a virtual address

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinInitWriteErr
item.description: Failure while writing the XBC CSR containing the link status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinInitReadErr
item.description: Failure while reading the XBC CSR containing the link status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricLinkInitIntermittentFailure

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaUpdateRtcFailedOlaCell
item.description: A failure occurred on the OLA cell during the attempt to synchronize its real time clock with the clock(s) in the existing partition Data field contains physical location of OLA cell

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSalInfoTimeout
item.description: Access to SAL error log procedure timed out because the log facility was busy processing a request from another CPU Data field indicates the SAL procedure ID

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhIprNotClearedOnCell
item.description: The PDH FPGA IPR is not cleared after a MAX_RD_CLR_IPR_TRIES on a cell The Data Filed in the Cell number See the next Chassis Code to see the MAX_RD_CLR_IPR_TRIES

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhIprClearAttempts
item.description: Indicated the PDH FPGA IPR is not cleared after a number of PDC attempts The Data Field contents the MAX_RD_CLR_IPR_TRIES Please look at the previous Chassis Code to see the Cell number

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootOlaUpdateRtcFailedExistingCell

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemIncompleteEchelon

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricRdPortStatePortInvalid

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricWrPortStatePortInvalid

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMainBpLpmFlt

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPalSetProcFeaturesFailed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtActiveLogNotFound
item.description: This chassis code shows that the error log space in the NVRAM has not been allocated for the current error event This will be emitted out whenever a error section is attempted to be logged without allocation of log space in NVRAM

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtReachedMaxErrorLogs
item.description: This indicates that the error logs for a particular event type have reached the maximum allowed to be stored in the NVRAM The event type is indicated in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtOldNoCellToDelete

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBpsOvercurrent
