item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBpsWarnOt
item.description: Data Bulk location

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtErmOutOfHeap
item.description: Error Response Mode code attempted a malloc of heap space that failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemDimmUnsupported
item.description: The dimm in the physical location given by the data field is not supported on this platform The dimm may not be supported by the hardware or the dimm may not have been properly qualified for this platform

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtOptsMallocError
item.description: The OPTIONS component was unable to allocate NVRAM memory in order to store a nonvolatile variable The storage area for NVRAM options may be full or there may be undetected corruption

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCellHwDegraded
item.description: A dimm or CPU has failed and is not operational for the system This event is emitted prior to determining if the cell should be integrated into the Partition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtNotIntegratingCell
item.description: A cpu or dimm error has been detected and the Complex Profile Cell Integration Table Cell integration policy says to not integrate the cell into the PD The data field is unused but the cell that emitted this event is the one that did not get integrated

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIoContextCorruptErr
item.description: The IO error context is corrupt This will impair IO error reporting

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIoRopeFatal
item.description: A rope went fatal from the SBA to the LBA If all the ropes go fatal the IO subsystem is dead Any IO below the rope will not be accessible The data field gives the physical location of the rope that went fatal Some ROPE_FATAL conditions will not cause the system to go down For Example a rope that has gone fatal during an OLAR operation will only cause warnings to the user not bring the partition down

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIoBusFatal
item.description: A PCI bus on the system is fatal Any device on this bus is unavailable Firmware was unable to complete card initialization due to an error Data field contains physical location of failed bus

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtIoRopeUnitFatal
item.description: One of the rope units in the SBA failed If all of the rope units fail then IO will not be available on this cell

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhFlashWriteEnableBitSetNowCleared
item.description: The System Flash Write Enable bit is incorrectly set and now clearing by PDC The Data field contains the value of PDH Miscellaneous Signal Register read before System Flash bit is cleared

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFirmwareInitError
item.description: System firmware encountered an error while trying to perform an operation during system initialization This event ID will always be emitted before an event ID that describes the status of the operation that failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMcIncompleteCpuSet
item.description: This means that all the cpus in the cell did not show up

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMcIncompleteCellSet
item.description: This means that all the cells did not rendezvous during the PD rendezvous The data part will contain the Expected data and the actual mask of the cells that rendezvoused

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMcTreeCheckFailed
item.description: The FW tree sanity check failed during the MCA error processing

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMcRegistryCheckFailed
item.description: This means that the registry sanity check failed during MCA error handling

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMcDuringOsMca
item.description: This means that MCA occurred while OS_MCA was performing error recovery

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMcMemDumpAbandon
item.description: This means that memory dump will be abandoned due to workaround for CN This happens when one of the Blocking timeout in the Processor input block of the Cell Controller occurs

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMcFwTreeNotComplete
item.description: The firmware tree is not complete and hence there will be no PD rendezvous

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtAcpiConfigMismatch
item.description: The firmware parameter that defines the ACPI configuration is inconsistent in at least one of the cells in the partition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinErrOrderStatusClrFailed
item.description: Writing the XIN_ERR_ORDER_STATUS register of the CC failed This is some sort of a hardware failure Data Field return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricAssertFabricInit
item.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric The firmware is not able to analyze this error Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command HPUX also saves these logs in the varstmlogsos directory and they can be viewed using the slview utility

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtInvalidPiromData
item.description: A value read by the PDHC from a CPU module's Processor Minor ROM was not within acceptable limits

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtSettingFreqRatiosError
item.description: An invalid parameter was specified when trying to set the cpu bus config register cpu frequencies ratio field Valid range is xe x

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtOptsBlockCksumError
item.description: The overhead structure of the OPTIONS block in NVRAM has a checksum error

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricColaLocalCcLinkNotInit
item.description: During a cell OLA the link on the local cell failed to initialize Data Field (my cell ) | XIN Link State

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinInitDisableWrError
item.description: An attempt to disable the fabric link failed because writing the CC CSR failed Data Field (cell ) | return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinErrMaskUnknownBkp
item.description: Could not determine the system type in order to write the appropriate error mask for the fabric link Data Field system type

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinWrErrMaskError
item.description: Failed writing the XIN error mask for CC's fabric link Data Field (cell ) | return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinRdErrMaskError
item.description: Could not read the XIN Link error mask register Data Field (cell ) | return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricInitCcLinkFailure
item.description: The CC to CC link initialization sequence has failed Data Field link init status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtResetCommandError
item.description: An error occurred while trying to notify the MP that a reset is about to occur (QPartitionReleaseBIB command) The status is in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricInitCcLinkDisableErr
item.description: A fabric access error occurred while trying to disable the CC to CC link on a single cell Medel system This cell will halt Data field error status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricSetPortStateGetSm4Err
item.description: While updating the Port State register the cell could not get the XBC semaphore Data field is (Port Num | XBC num | return status) Where return status is ( Success Access Failure Semaphore Owned By Another Semaphore Already Owned XBC Key Contention)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricSetPortStateRlsSm4Err
item.description: While updating the Port State register the cell could not get the XBC semaphore Data field is (Port Num | XBC num | return status) Where return status is ( Success Generic Failure)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricAssertFabricErr
item.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric The firmware is not able to analyze this error Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command HPUX also saves these logs in the varstmlogsos directory and they can be viewed using the slview utility

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinLinkAlreadyInit
item.description: While attempting to initialize the XIN link it was found to already be initialized A firmware assertion has failed The link will not be reinitialized and processing should continue as normal However the system could be confused at this point

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtNoCpuModulesFoundByPdhc
item.description: The PDHC FW could not detect any CPU modules on its Cell board so it is holding the Cell in reset

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuModCompatMismatch
item.description: The Cell has been disabled by PDHC FW because the CPU modules are not compatible Compatibility is determined based on data stored in the ScratchFRUID EEPROM on each CPU module The CPU module partition compatibility byte for each CPU module must be identical

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBadCpuModScratchCksum
item.description: The Cell has been disabled because of invalid data in a CPU module Scratch EEPROM PDHC FW checksums the FRUID data stored in each CPU module's Scratch EEPROM If a checksum fails the Cell is held in reset and will not boot The data field identifies the CPU module that failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhBatteryLowWarning
item.description: The battery voltage level is low for the cell This indicates that the NVRAM will not be saved if the power is removed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricRouteXbcCopyRoutingErr
item.description: There was an error while copying the routing for the XBC to the local XBC port The cell will reset Data (XBC port ) | (XBC num ) | return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCopyRdBackFailed
item.description: The read immediately after a write while copying routing registers failed Data whether or not the XBC Key was enabled

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricRtgCompleteSm4RlsErr
item.description: Failed to release a XBC Semaphore while marking each XBC in the complex to indicate that routing has completed Data (XBC num ) | return value

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricRtgCompleteWrFwdPrgErr
item.description: Writing this XBC's forward progress register failed Data (XBC num ) | return value

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricRtgCompleteSm4AccessErr
item.description: Failed to get a XBC Semaphore while marking each XBC in the complex to indicate that routing has completed Skipping this XBC Data (XBC num ) | return value

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricRtgCompleteTopologyErr
item.description: Reading this XBC's topology register failed Data Field (xbc num ) | return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricRouteTraversableCc2CcErr
item.description: Could not check the traversability between two cells on an XBCless platform Data field return status ( SUCCESS FALSE FAILURE)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricDataRouteTraversableCc2CcErr
item.description: Could not check the traversability between two cells on an XBCless platform Data field return status ( SUCCESS FALSE FAILURE)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseLclXinRdErr
item.description: While checking traversability of a cell back to back system there was an error reading the local cell's XIN block Data Field return status ( or )

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseRmtXinRdErr
item.description: While checking traversability of a cell back to back system there was an error reading the local cell's XIN block Data Field return status ( or )

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseLclNotInit
item.description: Could not traverse to the target cell The XIN link is either not initialized or is not connected to the target cell However the target cell is designated to be within the partition Data Field target cell | XIN link state register

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseRmtNotInit
item.description: Could not traverse to the target cell The XIN link is either not initialized or is not connected to the target cell However the target cell is designated to be within the partition Data Field target cell | XIN link state register

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricDisableXinLinkReadErr
item.description: Error reading the XIN_LINK_STATE register of the CC This occurred while verifying that the link had been disabled Data Field cell being read | return status from the CSR read

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricXinInitRetryReadErr
item.description: Failure while reading the XBC CSR containing the link status This occurred while attempting the retry process to get XBC to CC link initialized Data Field link init status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricAssertFabricCc
item.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric The firmware is not able to analyze this error Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command HPUX also saves these logs in the varstmlogsos directory and they can be viewed using the slview utility

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtCpuRestricted
item.description: The CPU that just completed self tests is functionally or performance restricted The data field contains the Self Test State Parameter The bit state field (bits ) can have the following values when this event is displayed Performance Restricted cpu still functions Functionally Restricted cpu doesn't function properly

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPdhInvalidRtcCleared
item.description: The RTC was found to be invalid and has been cleared

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtLstNotRun
item.description: System firmware requested that Late Self Tests be run by PAL but PAL returned that the tests did not actually run on the processor The data field indicates the status word returned by PAL

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootSetCellStateFabricFailure
item.description: An attempt to update the cell state has failed due to a fabric crossbar failure The cell number being updated in bits while the traversable cell set (those cells connected to the fabric) is returned in bits

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootResetCellStateFailure
item.description: Failed to reset a cell due to an error setting the cell's state The cell will not be reset with the other cells in the PD The cell number is reported in the data field

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtMemChipspareDeallocRank
item.description: SFW has detected that a DRAM is failing on the DIMM specified by the physical location The rank the failing DIMM is part of will be deallocated

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtClockFreqError
item.description: Internal CPU clocks are not valid when compared with the real time clock The data field contains the hex value of the elapsed time If this value is off a small percentage from the expected value (which is given in the next chassis code) the event is emitted

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricColaInitTraversableErr
item.description: Could not traverse the fabric to the cell being added Data field (chosen cell ) | return status where failure

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricAttemptFocusedReroute
item.description: A XBC port was found to be unhealthy on this reboot This cell will attempt to route around it Data field (local Cell ) | (local internal Port ) | (local XBC ) | XBC internal port number being routed around

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFabricCellRerouteNinfoErr
item.description: Error getting the XBC port's expected neighbor from a firmware table Data field (SUCCESS) or (FAILURE)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootWakeCpuIsCpuDeconfigErr
item.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition The data field contains the error return value from PDC function IsHCellCpuDeconfig()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootWakeCpuGetCountersErr
item.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition The data field contains the error return value from PDC function SleepAndWakeupCountersGet()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootWakeCpuGetStructAddrErr
item.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition The data field contains the error return value from PDC function PdhGetHCellStructAddr()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCheckCpu4CompletionErr
item.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition The data field contains the error return value from PDC function HasCpuCompletedWakeupTask()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCheckCpuGetStructAddrErr
item.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition The data field contains the error return value from PDC function PdhGetHCellStructAddr()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtReconfigResetScheduled
item.description: There is a need to reset the cell for reconfiguration but it cannot be done yet because the cell has not reported at BIB The Reset is being scheduled to be performed later

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtProfileWrongArchType
item.description: When processing the complex profile the an unexpected 'Architecture Type' was specified in the PAIA Arch field The actual data found is displayed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCheckCpuIsDeconfigErr
item.description: While trying to determine whether or not a particular processor has completed the task for which it was awakened PDC was unable to access the deconfig byte Minor about the target processor A processor should always be able to access this data in PDH memory for any processor on its own cell and for any processor on a cell that is alive in the partition Therefore PDC is either going to halt the cell or reset the partition because of this problem The data field contains the PDC error return status from IsHCellCpuDeconfig()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootCheckCpuGetCountersErr
item.description: While trying to determine whether or not a particular processor has completed the task for which it was awakened PDC was unable to access the CPU's sleep and wakeup counters for the target processor A processor should always be able to access this data in PDH memory for any processor on its own cell and for any processor on a cell that is alive in the partition Therefore PDC is either going to halt the cell or reset the partition because of this problem The data field contains the PDC error return status from SleepAndWakeupCountersGet()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootPdMonarchRtnFromSwSetFpErr
item.description: While trying to determine whether or not a particular processor has completed the task for which it was awakened PDC was unable to access the CPU's forward progress state (ie PST state) for the target processor A processor should always be able to access this data in PDH memory for any processor on its own cell and for any processor on a cell that is alive in the partition Therefore PDC is either going to halt the cell or reset the partition because of this problem The data field contains the PDC error return status from CpuFpSet()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootSlaveRtnFromFwSetFpErr
item.description: While trying to determine whether or not a particular processor has completed the task for which it was awakened PDC was unable to access the CPU's Forward Progress State (ie PST state) for the target processor A processor should always be able to access this data in PDH memory for any processor on its own cell and for any processor on a cell that is alive in the partition Therefore PDC is either going to halt the cell or reset the partition because of this problem The data field contains the PDC error return status from CpuFpSet()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootProblemBranchingToPgzLocation
item.description: At a certain point in PDC boot all of the processors in the partition except the PD monarch are put into a sleep and they remain there until they are awakened by the PD monarch at which time they read an architected location in Page Zero to find out where to branch to This gives the OS a mechanism by which to bring processors under its control and have it executing OS code This chassis log is sent if and when a problem is detected by PDC regarding the contents in the Page Zero location This means that PDC cannot branch to the location logged in the Page Zero location So PDC sends this chassis log and then the processor returns to sleep The data field is unused

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootBadCpuOrder
item.description: The Data Field contains the value used to determine a valid order

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootSlpWakeCntrsStructAddrErr
item.description: While trying to get the sleep counter and the wakeup counter for a particular processor which is kept in a data structure in PDH memory PDC was unable to determine the address to the data structure on the remote cell PDC is supposed to be able to calculate addresses to anything in PDH memory on other cells in the partition The data field contains the PDC error return status from a function called PdhGetHCellStructAddr()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootGetSleepTimeoutStructAddrErr
item.description: Error occurred accessing a PDC data structure Depending upon the situation the cell or entire partition will be reset The data field contains the return status for the function that encountered the error

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMoveSlavesDispatcherAddrErr
item.description: PDC is about to halt the cell because PDC was unable to determine the GNI address of the SlaveDispatcher function of PDC relocated to memory by PDC The data field contains the error return value from the function GetGniCodeAddrFromRomCodeAddr()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMoveSlavesCheckSlaveErr
item.description: PDC is about to halt the cell because at least one of the processors didn't complete the task for which they were awakened and then return to sleep The data field contains an error return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMoveSlavesFpSetAddrErr
item.description: PDC is about to halt the cell because PDC was unable to determine the GNI address of the CpuFpSet() function of PDC relocated to memory by PDC The data field contains the error return value from the function GetGniCodeAddrFromRomCodeAddr()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMoveSlavesFpSetErr
item.description: PDC is about to halt the cell because one or more of the slaves were unable to change their CPU FP state in PDH memory on the local cell The data field contains an error return status

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsStructAddrErr
item.description: PDC was trying to move the cell monarchs on each of the noncore cells into the Dispatcher but in order to do that the PD monarch needs to be able to read the CPU number of the cell monarch on each of the noncore cells which is kept in a data structure on each of the cells PDC was unable to get the address to the CELL_CPU_STATE structure in PDH memory in a cell in the partition The data field is the error return status from the PDC function called PdhGetHCellStructAddr()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsCheckSlaveErr
item.description: PDC is about to reset the partition because at least one of the processors didn't complete the task for which they were awakened and then return to sleep The data field contains the error return status from the PDC function CheckSingleSlave()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsFpSetAddrErr
item.description: PDC is about to reset the partition because it is unable to determine the GNI address for the CpuFpSet() function for one or more of the cells in the partition The data field contains the error return status from GetGniCodeAddrFromRomCodeAddr()

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsFpSetErr
item.description: PDC is about to reset the partition because one or more of the processors were unable to successfully modify their CPU FP State (aka their PST state) The data field contains the error return status from the CpuFpSet() function

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBootDualCoreInitFail
item.description: MX initialization failed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtPwrExptGreatrPwrBulk
item.description: The amount of power expected to be drawn by the currently operating hardware is greater than the rating of the currently operating Bulk Power Supplies (BPS) It is very likely that partitions may be powered down with no further warning to eliminate the excess power load

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtBulkPwrReduncLost
item.description: Bulk power supply (BPS) redundancy has been lost on one or more row(s) of power supplies in the complex The further loss of a single BPS or an AC grid will most likely result in the shutdown of partitions using the chassis that lost redundancy

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtACReduncLost
item.description: AC redundancy has been lost on one or more row(s) of power supplies in the complex The further loss of a single Bulk Power Supply (BPS) or the other AC grid will most likely result in the shutdown of partitions using the chassis that have lost redundancy

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFanCoolNotRedunc
item.description: The fans that cool a region of the system are not redundant If an additional fan fails in or is removed from this cooling domain the partitions on this system will be automatically shut down to prevent an over temperature condition

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFanInsufficientInCoolDomain
item.description: An insufficient number of fans are working in a cooling domain to permit system operation Running partitions will be shut down immediately to prevent system damage due to excessive heat (If the situation is corrected immediately it is possible to prevent system shutdown)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtOSNotUseAllProcs

item.name: Alarm Notification For : hpevtFMPUnexpctRstHasRcv
item.description: A Fabric Message Processor (FMP) has unexpectedly reset The system has recovered from the problem

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchLinkAliveChange
item.description: The switch has detected a change in the status of a port Possible Cause Solution If Port is nonfunctional Disconnected loose or defective SAN Cable Reattach or replace cable Distant switch or node powered off apply power to switch or node Distant daughter card defective replace defective daughter card If Port is functional Port is now active No action necessary If Port is intermittent Intermittent problems could be caused by a defective switch cable or daughter card Replace components until problem is isolated

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchNeighborValidationFailed
item.description: A ServerNet Switch failed neighbor validation on one of its ports The offending node will not be able to receive or transmit ServerNet data packets until the situation is corrected Possible Cause Solution Ports not configured If a port is not configured or disabled this event is generated whenever the topology is changed or firmware is updated The snetSwitchNeighborID will indicate that the link is down with LD If the snetSwitchNeighborID is AF this indicates the specified port is disabled and assumed failed If the specified port is not configured this event may be ignored Bad Node Run diagnostics to validate offending nodes Incorrect cabling verify cabling and correct if necessary Incorrect configuration switch configruation may be incorrect Reconfigure switch Node not added to SAN Offending node may not have been added to the SAN Run ServerNet II Administrative Utility to add node Incorrect SAN installation Offending node may not have been correctly added to SAN Run Administrator GUI to verify status and add if necessary To force the switch to rerun neighbor checks the user may have to manually cycle the power on the offending node

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchLinkLevelError
item.description: ServerNet Switch has detected link level errors Possible Cause Solution Bad node Run diagnostics to validate offending nodes are operating correctly Loose cable Check cable connections Bad cable Check for link error and replace cable Incorrect configuration Switch configuration may be incorrect Check EFIFO register to make sure it is set correctly for cable typelength Reconfigure switch if necessary Blabbering Node Run diagnostics to ensure that nodes at both ends of the cable are communicating properly Replace if necessary

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchPacketLevelError
item.description: ServerNet Switch has detected packet level errors Possible Cause Solution Bad node Run diagnostics to validate offending nodes are operating correctly Loose cable Check cable connections Bad cable Check for link error and replace cable Incorrect configuration Switch configuration may be incorrect Check router table to make sure it is set Reconfigure switch if necessary Blabbering Node Run diagnostics to ensure that nodes at both ends of the cable are communicating properly Replace if necessary Probing node A node may be trying to break into the network Isolate the node and verify SAN membership

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchIBCError
item.description: ServerNet Switch has detected IBC errors Possible Cause Solution Firmware upgrade or Configuration change This event can be safely ignored if preceding events indicate a firmware upgrade or configuration change caused the event to be generated Bad node Run diagnostics to validate offending nodes are operating correctly Loose cable Check cable connections Bad cable Check for link error and replace cable Incompatible software version Ensure that compatible versions of software and firmware are installed on the offending nodes Blabbering node Run diagnostics to ensure that nodes at both ends of the cable are communicating properly Replace if necessary Probing node A node may be trying to break into the network Isolate the node and verify SAN membership Switch ownership may be incorrect Check ownership cycle power on the offending switch to cause ownership update

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchAccessViolation
item.description: The switch has detected a request to or from an invalid id Possible Cause Solution Blabbering node Run diagnostics to ensure that nodes at both ends of the cable are communicating properly Replace if necessary Probing node A node may be trying to break into the network Isolate the node and verify SAN membership Switch ownership may be incorrect Check ownership cycle power on the offending switch to cause ownership update

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchOwnerChange
item.description: ServerNet Switch Primary Administrative node change Possible Cause Solution Primary node failed over If this was by user request this is a notification only and no action is needed Refer to snetSwitchSANManFailover for other possibilities Administrator changed primary Administrative node Notification only No action is necessary

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchFirmwareUpgrade
item.description: A firmware upgrade has been performed on the specified switch Possible Cause Solution Switch firmware has been upgraded Notification only No action in needed

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchSANManFailover
item.description: Administrative node failover has been detected The type of failure detected is reflected in the event type Possible Cause Solution Primary or backup administrative node has failed if powered off apply power If hung reboot node If doing maintenance this is a notification message only Restart node when maintenance is complete Backup administrative node not configured use the ServerNet II Administrative Utility to define a backup

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchTopologyConfigUpdate
item.description: Configuration of the ServerNet topology has changed Possible Cause Solution Switch or end node configuration has been updated Notification only no action required May also be generated when switch firmware is upgraded or new primary or backup nodes are designated

item.name: Alarm Notification For : snetSwitchFanFailure
item.description: ServerNet Switch detected a fan failure The power module should be replaced immediately to prevent switch component damage Possible Cause Solution A switch fan has failed replace switch power module to prevent switch component damage

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI1
item.description: Symbios SCSI Agent is up

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI2
item.description: Symbios SCSI Agent is down

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI3
item.description: New SCSI Controller discovered This trap signifies that the agent has detected that a new SCSI Controller has been added The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller The variable controllerName indicates the controller name The variable managerName indicates the manager name

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI4
item.description: The SCSI Controller has been replaced This trap signifies that the agent has detected that the controller at the specified index has been replaced with another adapter of a different adapter family The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller The variable controllerName indicates the controller name The variable managerName indicates the manager name

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI5
item.description: The SCSI Controller has Failed This trap signifies that the agent has detected that the SCSI controller has failed The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI6
item.description: The SCSI Controller has recovered This trap signifies that the agent has detected that the previously failed SCSI controller has recovered The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI8
item.description: A new SCSI Device has been Discovered This trap signifies that the agent has detected a new SCSI device The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller The variable scsiTarget indicates the SCSI Target number of the device The variable scsiLun indicates the SCSI LUN of the device The variable vendorName indicates the device vendor The variable productName indicates the device product name

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI10
item.description: The SCSI Device has been Replaced This trap signifies that a detected SCSI device has been swapped If the device supports the SCSI serial number page this trap is sent even if the replaced device is identical The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller The variable scsiTarget indicates the SCSI Target number of the device The variable scsiLun indicates the SCSI LUN of the device The variable vendorName indicates the device vendor The variable productName indicates the device product name

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI7
item.description: The SCSI Device has Failed This trap signifies that the agent has detected that a SCSI device has failed The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller The variable scsiTarget indicates the SCSI Target number of the device The variable scsiLun indicates the SCSI LUN of the device

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI9
item.description: The SCSI Device has Recovered This trap signifies that a previously failed SCSI device has started working again The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller The variable scsiTarget indicates the SCSI Target number of the device The variable scsiLun indicates the SCSI LUN of the device

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI11
item.description: A SMART event has occurred on a device This trap signifies that the agent has detected that a SMART event has occurred The variable scsiController indicates the logical index of the controller The variable scsiTarget indicates the SCSI Target number of the device The variable scsiLun indicates the SCSI LUN of the device The variable vendorName indicates the device vendor The variable productName indicates the device product name The variable scsiSmartData indicates the sense Minor

item.name: Alarm Notification For : symSCSI12
item.description: There was an internal Symbios error Please restart the Symbios agent

item.name: Alarm Notification For : zesalinkUp
item.description: A LinkUp trap signiifies that the status of the line has changed from STOPPED to STARTED state

item.name: Alarm Notification For : zesalinkDown
item.description: A LinkDown trap signiifies that the status of the line has changed from STARTED to STOPPED state

item.name: Alarm Notification For : zhrmTrapDeviceStateChange
item.description: When zhrmDevUnTrapEnable is set to this trap is generated whenever the status of any device represented in the hrDevice group changes

item.name: Alarm Notification For : zhrmRAMThreshold
item.description: When zhrmThrRAMTrapEnable is set to this trap is generated whenever the utilization of any RAM storage area represented in the hrStorage group reaches or exceeds a high threshold (represented by the value of zhrmThrRAMHighValue in the zhrmThreshold group) or reaches or falls below a low threshold (represented by the value of zhrmThrRAMLowValue in the zhrmThreshold group

item.name: Alarm Notification For : zhrmDiskThreshold
item.description: When zhrmThrDiskTrapEnable is set to this trap is generated whenever the utilization of any disk represented in the hrStorage group reaches or exceeds a high threshold (represented by the value of zhrmThrDiskLowValue in the zhrmThreshold group) or reaches or falls below a low threshold (represented by the value of zhrmThrDiskLowValue in the zhrmThreshold group)

trigger.name: Alert destination blacklisted The Server Manager board modem has blacklisted an alert...
trigger.description: Alert destination blacklisted The Server Manager board modem has blacklisted an alert destination phone number Once blacklisted that alert destination is no longer available for use as an alert destination Blacklisting which only occurs in international modems is a requirement imposed by certain European countries on modems to prevent a phone number from being dialed multiple times without getting a connection The number of attempts required to have blacklisting occur vary from country to country Once an alert destination has been blacklisted the only way to remove the blacklisted phone number is to remove power from the modem On external modems this is a trival task When a blacklisting occurs on the Server Manager board's internal modem the task is slightly more difficult as the modem gets power from the Server Manager board To remove power from the Server Manager board's internal modem the Server Manager board must be forced into Dormant Mode This is an operating mode used to conserve battery life which is entered automatically if the board looses power To cause the board to enter Dormant Mode the following steps should be performed ) Disable alerting via CPQCAUINLM ) Disable async communication via CPQCAUINLM ) Down the server ) Exit to DOS (if applicable) ) Shut power off to the computer ) Wait minutes before restoring power Once the minutes has expired and power to the computer has been restored the modem will have flushed its blacklist and the board's alerting functions will work as expected
